title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: Add cooked rice to milk; heat to scalding point in top of double boiler.
Beat yolks with sugar.
Add rice and milk mixture to yolk and sugar (slowly), beating fast.
Pour all back into top of double boiler; cook until thick.
Fold in raisins or chopped fruits, if desired.
Place in buttered casserole.
Cover with meringue; brown.

title: low-calorie french dressing
directions: Combine in a jar.
Shake well to mix and chill.
Makes 1 pint. Only 46 calories per tablespoon.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one
at
a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk
and flour (sifted with salt) alternately, beginning and ending
with flour.
Add
vanilla
and lemon extracts.
Spoon into 10-inch tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger along with onions and garlic.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, breaking up with spoon, kidney beans and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes to blend flavors.
Spoon 1 cup chili mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cut 4 tortillas lengthwise, arrange flat edges against sides of dish to cover bottom of pan.
Spoon half the remaining chili mixture over tortilla layer.
Halve 3 tortillas and cover chili layers; sprinkle with lettuce and cheese.
Halve remaining tortillas and cover previous layer.
Spoon remaining chili mixture over tortillas. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with additional shredded lettuce and cheese.

title: onion soup
directions: Slice onions and brown in butter until translucent.
Add cans of beef broth soup, bouillon cubes and sherry.
Heat through and put in soup crocks.

title: macaroni and tuna casserole
directions: Add cream cheese to soup and cook slightly until mixed.
Add milk, tuna, onion and cooked macaroni.
Put in 3-quart casserole. Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: never fail cheese souffle
directions: Blend mayonnaise, flour, milk, egg yolk, salt and cornstarch. Add cheese and stir to blend.

title: sweet-sour meat loaf
directions: To prepare sauce, combine ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat until melted and well blended.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all meat loaf ingredients.
Mold into a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Pour about 1/2 sauce over meat loaf and reserve remainder for another use.

title: coney sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Grind hot dogs and onions together.
Mix all together and simmer.
The longer you simmer it, the better it is!

title: korean beef(bul-go-ki)
directions: Mix the beef slices and sugar together.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a separate bowl.
Put everything together.
Cook on top of grill or in a frying pan.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Mix soups, milk, hot sauce and onion. Grease the bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Line with half
of tortillas. Add half of chicken meat, then layer with half of soup mixture. Repeat. Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: overnight cinnamon buns
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle in nuts and raisins, then arrange frozen dough rolls on top.
Melt butter, brown sugar, honey and cinnamon over low heat.
Pour over rolls.
Cover with plastic wrap; leave at room temperature overnight.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert onto plate.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, salt and pepper together.
Beginning with soup mixture, layer soup mixture and chicken.
This usually makes 2 layers, depending on the size of your casserole dish.
Mix melted margarine and Ritz cracker crumbs and top the casserole with them. Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yam soup
directions: Boil yams in water until tender; remove from heat and drain. Peel immediately under cold running water.
Place yams in a mixing bowl; mash with a potato masher until smooth.
Set aside.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and cinnamon.
Add sifted flour, soda and baking powder.
Stir in nuts and zucchini.
Pour into large pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: nine day slaw
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar, oil, celery seed and salt. Pour over the chopped ingredients and refrigerate.

title: apple pie or tart
directions: Mix and boil until smooth and thick.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn back temperature to 350°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften, then mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate 1 hour and serve.
Great with fresh fruits like apples, bananas, strawberries, etc.
Dip and eat.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together until it begins to foam.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: beet and onion salad
directions: Drain beets.
Mix with onion slices.
Dress with vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper.

title: chicken and green noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water for 30 minutes or until tender. Drain; reserve stock.
Bone chicken and cut into bite size pieces. Set aside.
Cook noodles in stock until tender; drain and set aside.
You can put a pat of butter in the noodles so they won't stick together.

title: hot dried beef dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with milk.
Mix in other ingredients.
Spread mixture into 8-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers or sturdy potato chips. Double recipe for a crowd.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for about 1/2 hour and serve.

title: sink toast
directions: You will need 1 kitchen knife and 1 pop-up toaster that doesn't pop up.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and cherry pie filling.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: delicious white bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast; blend well.
In small saucepan, heat water and oil until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in an additional 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour until dough pulls cleanly away from sides of bowl.
On floured surface, knead in 1/2 to 1 cup flour until dough is smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Place dough in greased bowl; cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel.

title: diabetic strawberry pie
directions: Blend milk with pudding mix.
Add grated orange rind.
Let stand 5 minutes and pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Arrange berries/fruit over pudding before serving.
Makes 1 pie.

title: ellen's smoked salmon spread
directions: Cut 1/2 of the salmon into chunks.
Dice the remaining salmon. Place cottage cheese in a fine-mesh sieve and press on it to remove excess moisture.
Transfer cottage cheese to a food processor.
Add the salmon chunks, vodka, lemon juice, mustard and horseradish.
Process until smooth.
Transfer the mixture to bowl and fold in the diced salmon.
Refrigerate until chilled.
May be prepared ahead and stored, covered, in the refrigerator for up to 2 days.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt butter and caramels together; add nuts.
Mix cake as directed.
Pour 1/2 batter in long pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Spread caramel mix on cake; pour remainder of cake batter over caramel and bake at 350° until done.

title: oven fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper; set aside.
Combine egg and water; beat well.
Dip tomatoes in egg mixture and dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Lightly coat a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Place tomatoes in a single layer in pan. Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: hamburger casserole for crock-pot
directions: Place layers of vegetables in the order given in crock-pot. Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Put the lightly browned ground beef on top of the celery.
Mix tomato soup with the water and pour into pot.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or on high 2 to 4 hours.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until dough forms; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Beat cheeses with mixer.
Add lemon juice and beat until smooth.
Add beef extract and onion; mix well.
Blend in mayonnaise.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown chopped meat, onion and pepper.
Drain off fat.
Blend in pizza sauce, garlic salt and oregano.
Put mixture in a greased, 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: micro fish special
directions: Wash and dry fish with paper towel.
Spread mayonnaise on fish.
Mix Worcestershire sauce or soy sauce with bread crumbs. Sprinkle over fish.
Bake, covered, with wax paper for 4 to 6 minutes.

title: coffee-time twists
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Heat cream to lukewarm; combine with sugar, shortening, salt and soda.
Add 1 cup flour.
Beat. Add yeast and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in rest of flour.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead until smooth.
Roll into 24 x 6-inch rectangle, 1/4-inch thick.
Fold over lengthwise half of dough. After combining brown sugar and cinnamon, butter dough; spread sugar mix on half.
Cut into 1-inch strips.
To form rolls, hold strips at both ends and twist in opposite directions.
Place on greased pan; set in warm place to rise.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While warm, ice with powdered sugar icing.

title: tomato soup
directions: Heat tomatoes in a large saucepan, breaking up large pieces. In another pan, melt margarine.
Add flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and cook until bubbly.
Do not brown.
Remove from heat and add milk to equal amount of tomatoes.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened, 5 to 7 minutes.
Off burner, add mixture to hot tomatoes slowly, stirring constantly to prevent curdling.
Return to burner.
Bring to boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Serve with a teaspoon of butter in each bowl.

title: orange cider
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water, cider, brown sugar, cloves and cinnamon. Simmer on medium-low heat until heated through and flavors blend.
Remove from heat.
Add orange and spice tea bags. Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Remove tea bags, cloves and cinnamon.
Serve warm.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook the rice, water and salt in a small saucepan until done. Drain off water and set in refrigerator until well cooled. Then add the marshmallows and pineapple. Fold in the whipping cream.

title: crock pot sirloin tip casserole
directions: Mix beef, soup and onion soup mix in crockpot.
Place potatoes on top, turning them once to cover with the soup mixture.

title: make ahead chicken supreme
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in beef; put a strip of bacon on top of each.
Place in a shallow pan.
Combine soup, sherry and sour cream; pour mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 30 additional minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Make a well and add the egg, butter, juice and water.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in cranberries, nuts and orange peel.
Bake in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 325° for about 1 hour or until the bread tests done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan to wire rack.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to a hard boil, stir in cream of tartar and dissolve; put in Hi Ho crackers and boil for two minutes.
Pour in pie crust and slice a little butter on top; flavor with spice. Put on top crust and bake in 400° oven until crust is brown.

title: chicken veggie casserole
directions: In skillet, boil chicken with onion for about 1 hour.
Put in casserole dish.
Place chicken on bottom.
Cook cauliflower and broccoli as directed on bag.
Drain.
Place cauliflower and broccoli on top of chicken.
Dice potatoes and place in casserole dish.
Place baby carrots, also peas (drain peas from juice).
Add 2 cans of broccoli with cheese.
Add 1 can of milk.
Salt and pepper for taste.
Bake at 350°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 2 pizza pans or 3 small cake pans with foil. Combine 1/2 cake mix with water, eggs, butter and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly. Fold in nuts and rest of cake mix.
Divide mixture in pans. Spread this out in pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes. Cool and remove from foil. Spread Cool Whip on top of crust.
Cut fruit and decorate the pizzas with this fruit.
May add orange marmalade (water it down).

title: roast beaver
directions: A 10 to 12 pound dressed young beaver will fit whole in a roaster.
For larger carcasses, cut into 4 to 6 pieces.
Place on rack to keep off the bottom of the pan.
Salt and pepper.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion. Cook macaroni. Layer macaroni, sauce, meat, pepperoni and cheese in casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lamb shanks
directions: Place shanks in roaster with a lid.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over shanks.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours or until tender.
I prefer the smaller shanks.

title: quick and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine
peanut
butter, sugar and beaten eggs in bowl; mix well.
Drop
by
teaspoonfuls,
2-inches	apart,	onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped into water. Bake at
325° for
10 minutes or until light brown.
Cook and then cool on cookie sheet for at least 2 minutes.
Yields 24.

title: garbanzo bean soup
directions: Brown chopped onion in olive oil.
Add onions and ham bone to 2 quarts water and simmer for 45 minutes.
Remove ham bone and remove meat from bone and place back in water.
Add beans, chorizos, potatoes and Vigo seasoning.
Cook on low 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: valentine tarts
directions: Place cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Line muffin tin with paper liner. Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Top with a dash of pie filling. Chill.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Wash bell peppers and cut a circle around the stems and just pull out the stem.
The core and most of the seeds will pull out with the stem.
Shake out any left behind seeds.
Place peppers in a baking dish with the openings up, and prepare stuffing.

title: reuben breads appetizer
directions: Combine the ingredients in mixing bowl.
(Be sure to cut the American and Swiss cheeses into small squares.)
Spread mixture onto party ryes.
Bake at 400° or until bubbling and serve!

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy cheezy zucchini dish
directions: Spread zucchini on bottom of pan; top with onion, then cheese. Bake at 350° until zucchini is tender.
At last minute, sprinkle Special K cereal on top to brown lightly.

title: corn filling
directions: Mix and place in greased casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Cover the cereal with the mixture; place in paper bag with sugar and toss to coat the cereal.

title: zucchini mexicali
directions: Note:
Quantities may be altered as desired.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, and dry taco mix.
Put into a casserole dish.
Add picante sauce to top, then follow with cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
Chill.

title: white moon cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt 3 times.
Cream sugar and butter together, adding milk and flour, etc., leaving egg whites last.
Top with Brown Sugar Frosting.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and sausage.
Pour half of mixture into hot, greased 10-inch skillet, then layer meat and cheese. Top off with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: chili beans
directions: Simmer slowly for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar and add well beaten eggs.
Blend cinnamon, cloves and flour.
Put the baking soda in the blackberries and add to the mixture, alternately with the flour mixture.
Add nuts and raisins if desired.
Bake in 9 inch layer pans or a 9 x 13 inch pan at 325° for 45 minutes or until done. Frost with favorite frosting or dust with powdered sugar.
Serves 20.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, milk and salt in medium-size saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cover pan and cook allowing steam to wash down the sugar crystals that cling to side of pan.

Uncover pan; insert candy thermometer and cook without stirring until candy thermometer reads 236° where syrup, when dripped into very cold water, forms a soft ball that flattens on removal from water.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Cool syrup until lukewarm (110°).
Add vanilla, peanut butter and nuts.
Beat until candy begins to thicken and loses its high gloss.
Turn immediately into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Score with sharp knife.
Cut into small squares when cool.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Toss first 5 ingredients together.
Melt margarine and seasoned crumbs together.
Add 1/2 of crumb mixture to first mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients. Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (two 9-inch pans).

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix.
Add cauliflower and chopped green onions.
Add sliced radishes if desired and water chestnuts; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: wild plum muffins
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and baby food. Stir just until mixed. Spray mini muffin pans with Pam.
Fill pans with batter. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 dozen.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots; boil until tender in salted water. Drain and layer in baking dish with onion and pepper, finishing with carrots on top.
Bring soup, sugar and oil to a boil; pour over carrots and refrigerate.
Will keep a month in refrigerator.

title: quick fruit salad or dessert
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill and serve as salad or dessert.

title: pork chop meal
directions: Trim fat and bones from pork chops.
Put potatoes in bottom of dish.
Layer with pork chops.
Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash and Butter Buds.
Slice onion over pork chops.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over this.
Put chopped cabbage over this.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups hot water; pour over everything.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until potatoes are done.

title: easy and light banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on the package.
Add 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and crushed vanilla wafers.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Brown together ground beef and onion; drain well.
Add all remaining ingredients; stir well.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Butter pie pan with cold butter.
Mix egg, flour, sugar, milk and melted butter.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 300° or 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple-nut muffins
directions: Grease 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups boiling water.
After completely dissolved, add 2 1/2 cups cold water.
Set in refrigerator until it begins to set up.
Fold in pineapple and peaches.
Let completely gel.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Mix dry mix, eggs and apple pie filling until well blended. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Add 1/2 teaspoon apple pie spice to your favorite cream cheese icing and frost cooled cake.

title: cold weather chili
directions: Lightly brown ground beef in a 5-quart pan or Dutch oven; add salt and pepper.
Add onion and green peppers and cook until soft. Add tomato sauce and paste; dilute with water to desired consistency.
Add all remaining ingredients to chili mixture. Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove one cup of mixture and process in blender until smooth; pour processed mixture back into chili, stir well.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Peel and cut apples about the size of a thimble. Sprinkle in 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar; set aside.

title: spaghetti with crab sauce
directions: Saute the chopped celery, parsley, garlic and onion in the olive oil until delicately browned.
Use a skillet that will be large enough to hold the spaghetti.
Add the tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, paprika, salt and pepper and simmer for an hour, uncovered.
Pick over crab meat for bits of shell; wash and drain thoroughly.
Add the crab and sherry wine to the tomato mixture and simmer until it bubbles.
Cook the spaghetti in a large kettle of boiling, salted water.
When it is just tender, drain (do not rinse) and add to the tomato and crab sauce.
Serve covered with grated Parmesan cheese on a well heated platter.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oatmeal raspberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish.
Beat margarine and brown sugar in a large bowl (at medium speed) until light and fluffy (about 1 minute).
Add oats, flour, salt, and baking soda to the bowl; mix until crumbly.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add sugar.
Mix and cool slightly. Add beaten eggs and stir in.
Add flour and cocoa; mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 7-inch square aluminum pan or a 7 x 10-inch oblong.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Watch; do not overcook.
Cut into squares while still warm.
When cold, store in cookie tin.

title: caramel banana nut pie
directions: Boil the unopened can of milk slowly in full pot of water for 1 hour.
Let water come to full boil before timing.
Slice the bananas.
Place the bananas and nuts into cooked pie shell.
Let milk cool.
Open and pour over bananas and nuts.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Let come to a boil for 1 minute. Add other 4 ingredients.
Mix and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together last 3 ingredients and let set for 1/2 hour.
Cut up broccoli into small flowerets and cut up good part of stem into small pieces.
Place broccoli, raisins, peanuts and red onion in bowl.
Add dressing and gently toss together.
Chill.
It's better to make a day before.

title: ginny's peanut butter pies
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding according to directions on package. Add peanut butter (while pudding is hot) to pudding and stir until smooth and dissolved.
Pour pudding into the two graham cracker crusts.
Store in refrigerator until cool.
Add Cool Whip to the top of each pie.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes two pies.

title: chicken pulao
directions: Place about 3 tablespoons of oil into a large frying pan with 5 or 6 whole cloves, 3 or 4 peppercorns, 4 or 5 whole cardamon seed that have been popped open or 1/8 teaspoon ground cardamon, 2 or 3 pieces of whole cinnamon sticks, 3 sliced medium onions, 2 garlic cloves and 1-inch fresh ginger root, cut up finely.
Fry for 2 to 3 minutes to bring out the flavor and add cut up chicken pieces, then fry for another 5 to 6 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon turmeric powder, 1 teaspoon ground coriander, cleaned and washed rice and enough liquid to make 4 cups.
Put on a tight lid and cook until the rice is almost finished and then add 6 tablespoons yogurt.
Mix thoroughly and continue cooking until the liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
(Add liquid if necessary.)
Serve on platter; garnish with fried onions (crisp), almonds, raisins and coconut slices.

title: ting-a-lings
directions: Toss peanuts and noodles together in a 2-quart glass casserole. Melt butterscotch pieces in a 1-quart glass measuring pitcher in microwave oven (about 3 minutes at High).
Stir until smooth.
Add to peanut mixture and toss gently until coated.
Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill to harden.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onions in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook.
The longer you cook the sauce, the better it will taste.

title: spritz
directions: Cream together butter and sugar, then add egg, vanilla and extract.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture. Add any color food coloring.
Don't chill.
Press out with cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Butter bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Line with marshmallows. Melt Candy Quic.
Add pecans.
Pour over marshmallows.

title: rhubarb and strawberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry. Fill with rhubarb and strawberries tossed together.
Combine sugar and flour and sprinkle over rhubarb and strawberries.
Shake the pan to distribute the sugar.
Dot with butter.

title: "dumplins"
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Add butter and eggs.
Mix and form a stiff dough.
Roll out and cut into strips and squares.
Drop into broth that is boiling.
When all dumplins are added, cover and turn burner off and allow to remain covered for 15 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve.

title: white chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Cook chicken with oil, onions and garlic until tender.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips and top with Monterey Jack cheese, shredded.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and oil for 2 to 3 minutes and stir well. Pour over chopped vegetables in large bowl.
Add drained vegetables and stir well.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Heat small saucepan of water to boiling.
Add broccoli to pan and cook 2 minutes; drain.
Combine Ricotta and Mozzarella in small bowl.
Spread over prepared pizza crust, leaving 1-inch border.
Arrange 1/4 cup broccoli in center, then arrange remaining broccoli around edge of Ricotta.
Spoon tomato sauce over exposed Ricotta mixture.
Sprinkle with Romano or Parmesan cheese.
Bake pizza 10 minutes.
Cut into 8 wedges.

title: breakfast pockets
directions: Whisk eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into skillet, stirring until softly scrambled.
Crumble in bacon.
Stuff pitas with cheese and then eggs.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Beat cream cheese in mixer until smooth.
Add potatoes and rest of ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Spoon into buttered casserole.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: summery noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Saute garlic and vegetables in butter in skillet or saucepan until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Add noodles and heat gently.
Makes 4 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Mix in order in punch bowl. Serves approximately 25 (6-ounce) beverage cups. Punch color can be changed by the flavor of Hawaiian Punch used.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in large mixing bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or when cake springs back and pulls away from sides.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Spoon hot butter glaze over warm cake.

title: southern scalloped corn
directions: Melt butter in pan you bake corn in.
Beat eggs well and add both cans of corn, sour cream.
Mix well.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix oleo, flour and chopped nuts together and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine oil, dressing mix and spices together and let stand for one hour.
Place crackers in airtight container.
Pour oil mixture over crackers and shake well.
Leave crackers covered for at least 24 hours, shaking occasionally.

title: cheese pudding
directions: To make white sauce, put 6 tablespoons butter or margarine in a saucepan and heat until melted.
Remove from heat and add 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons flour, slowly stirring to make a smooth paste.
Return to heat and slowly add 3 cups milk while stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.

title: pfeffernuesse
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in order given; have ingredients at room temperature.
Mix spices with 2 cups of flour.
Add to first mixture; mix well.
Add remainder of flour, one cup at a time, mixing well.
Dough will be very stiff.
Chill.
Take a small piece of dough and roll between hands and board into round, pencil-like shape, about 1/2 inch in diameter.
Slice off 1/4 to 1/2-inch pieces.
Lay on lightly-greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: corn bake
directions: Saute together the onion, green pepper and margarine.
Add the eggs, creamed corn, kernel corn and corn muffin mix.
Pour into a 2-quart dish.
Top with sour cream and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: snow biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and melted Crisco.
Then add flour.
Roll out on floured wax paper and cut into biscuit size.
Let rise 45 to 60 minutes.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown on top.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: quick barbecue bake(beef or low-fat turkey)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook beef or turkey and 1/2 c. of the onion in 10-inch skillet until meat is brown; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Stir baking mix, milk and eggs until blended.
Pour over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining onion.
Bake 25 - 27 min. or until crust is light golden brown.
Makes 8 - 10 servings.

title: night before french toast casserole
directions: Use extra butter to grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cut bread into 1-inch thick slices and arrange in one layer in bottom of pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs with remaining ingredients except butter.
When thoroughly mixed, pour over bread in pan. Cover with foil and refrigerate 4 to 36 hours.

title: hungarian chicken paprikash
directions: In a large skillet, saut onions over medium heat in butter until golden on edges.
Remove onions from pan.
Brown the chicken breasts in remaining butter and return onions when chicken is lightly browned.
Add paprika and chicken broth.
Cover skillet with well fitting lid and lower heat.
Cook for about 30 to 45 minutes, checking to make sure broth is not completely cooked out. When broth has reduced by about 50 percent, add heavy cream and remove from heat.
Mix cream with onion, broth and chicken.
Add more paprika if mixture is not a beautiful pink/orange gravy.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over cooked extra wide egg noodles.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat first two ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Mix and freeze all but soda.
Take out of freezer about 2 hours before serving.
Freeze in half gallon container.
Add about 1 1/2 quarts to each half gallon.
Break up frozen juice with potato masher. Serves 70.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt oleo in medium size saucepan.
Chop onion in food processor.	Saute onion in melted oleo for a few minutes.
Add the Ro-Tel tomatoes and tomatoes that have been chopped in food processor.	Let simmer until a nice dipping consistency.
Add Velveeta cheese that has been cubed.
Cook until cheese is melted, being careful not to let burn.
Serve with Tostitos corn chips.

title: cinnamon swirl bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk; stir in 1/4 cup sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in egg, half the flour and yeast.
Beat with a spoon until smooth.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in a bowl and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch down and let rest 10 minutes.
Roll dough into a rectangle; brush with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up starting at narrow side; pinch ends and place in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Brush top with butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon if desired.
Let rise until doubled and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost, if desired.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes or in microwave oven 10 or 15 minutes.
Serves 4 portions.

title: deep south barbecue sauce
directions: Cook slowly until butter melts.
Keep warm.
May be used in outdoor barbecuing to baste meat or an oven roast.
May be sliced and simmered in sauce. Good with pork, lamb or beef.
Sufficient for four of five pounds of meat.

title: virginia's banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add mashed bananas and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and combine.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with cream cheese if desired.

title: sauteed peppers
directions: Combine green and red pepper strips and mushrooms in 2 qt. casserole.
Add olive oil, garlic, pimento, salt and pepper. Cover.

title: cherry pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, salt and add cherries.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Add dots of butter.
Cover with top crust; cover edges well.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce to 350° and bake 40 to 45 minutes longer.

title: plum sauce
directions: *May also use plum jelly or jam in place of preserves.

title: pineapple sponge cake
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Beat egg whites and salt until forms moist peaks.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar and beat well.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks until thick and fluffy. Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar.
Stop mixer.

title: swedish butter cookies(spritz cookies)
directions: Sift flour with baking powder.
Cream the butter, sugar and salt.
Add the egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add sifted ingredients in small amounts.
Mold with cookie press on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 45 cookies.

title: potato cheese croquettes
directions: Beat eggs and potatoes until frothy.
Stir in cheese and seasoning.
Shape as desired.
Dip in bread crumbs.
Fry in shallow, hot fat until brown.

title: bisquick master mix
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cream of tartar, salt and baking powder. Cut in shortening.
Mix until consistency of corn meal.
Store in a sealed container.
Yield:
13 cups.

title: nobodys
directions: In saucepan, put cocoa, sugar, milk and butter.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add crunchy peanut butter, quick oats and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: washboard cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, brown sugar and egg.
Stir together baking soda and water; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and flour; mix well.
Shape into walnut sized balls. Place on greased cookie sheet; flatten with a fork that has been dipped in water.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Cool on waxed paper. Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: hamburger skillet
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger; drain.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and onion; heat until boiling. Combine Bisquick and milk; beat until stiff but sticky.
Drop by rounded tablespoons atop boiling meat mixture.
Cover and let simmer about 12 minutes.
Do not lift lid during cooking.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: electric peach ice cream
directions: Combine 1/2 of peaches and 1/4 cup milk in blender.
Process until smooth.
Transfer to a medium bowl.
Repeat procedure with remaining peaches and 1/4 cup milk.
Set aside.
Combine remaining 2 1/2 cups milk and next 3 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in peach mixture and nectar.
Pour into container of 4-quart electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: sweet potato hickory nut cobbler
directions: Make crust with 5 heaping tablespoonfuls flour, 1 heaping tablespoonful shortening and water to mix.
Roll on cloth (1/2 of mixture), add to half of potatoes and brown in 400° oven.
Then repeat with remainder of potatoes.
Add top crust and bake.
Serve hot.

title: zucchini squares
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, oil, eggs, flour, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well, then add baking powder, baking soda, oats and salt.
Mix well until blended.
Fold in nuts.
Spoon batter into greased sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool in pan, then add icing.

title: quick quiche
directions: Grate Swiss cheese and sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion into a 10-inch pie plate.
Place in a blender the remaining ingredients; blend for 15 seconds.
Bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Slice and serve.

title: snow balls
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and salt. Add nuts.
Mix all together.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream
butter
thoroughly;
gradually
add sugar.
Beat egg yellows
and add.
Mix soda, salt and cream of tartar with flour and
add
to batter.
Beat egg whites and add.
Beat all this with mixture.
Now, stir with hands real good as it gets thicker with mixture.
Bake in oven at 200° to 250°, depending on how the heat is on your oven.
Cut heat back if cake starts browning too quickly.
Cook for 3 hours or until cake is done. Bake in deep tube pan.

title: chocolate chip meringue drops
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Line 3 baking sheets with parchment or foil.
Beat egg whites until they hold stiff peaks.
Beat in the sugar one tablespoon at a time.
Then add vanilla.
Reduce mixer speed to low and add cocoa.
Fold in the chocolate chips with a rubber spatula.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets, 1 inch apart and bake for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and dry the cookies in the oven 2 hours longer.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 40 cookies.
You can substitute 1/2 cup chopped nuts for the chocolate chips and add a pinch each of nutmeg and cinnamon.

title: sweet-sour dressing
directions: Clean and cook carrots until done (slice them).
Mix remaining ingredients together in blender until well blended.
Mix well and pour over cooked carrots.
Better the second day.

title: fruit dip
directions: Set cream cheese out until room temperature.
Add whipped cream and cinnamon and mix well.
Chill 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken on all sides in oil; spoon off all but 2 tablespoons drippings from skillet.
Add sausage, tomatoes, water, onion, garlic, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Cover; cook over low heat several minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and cook 30 minutes longer or until chicken is done and all liquid is gone. Yields 8 servings.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Set cream cheese out to soften. Mix in marshmallow cream and orange juice. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: date krispies
directions: Mix together.
Cook over slow heat 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add 3 cups Rice Krispies and stir well.
Spread on a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Press firmly into pan and sprinkle top with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.
Enjoy!

title: fried cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage to about medium fine; set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Let drain; break into small pieces.
Add cabbage to bacon drippings; saute, stirring constantly.
Add
vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Serve immediately with bacon sprinkled on top of the cabbage.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done and tender.
Pour off all but about 6 cups of broth and set the broth aside.
Remove chicken to cool and debone.
Add bell peppers, onion and celery; cook until tender. Cook spaghetti in broth until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add soup to spaghetti and broth.
Cut Velveeta into pieces; stir until melted.
Add extra broth in if needed.
(This is great frozen for a second meal.)

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Mix together and spread over and between 3 layer cake.

title: chicken loaf
directions: In bowl, mix together ingredients; mix well.
Turn into a 5 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until done in center.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut in wedges and serve.

title: sweet potato compose
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until soft.
Add sugar, eggs, margarine, flavoring, few chopped nuts, raisins and coconut.
Spoon out on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until set real well.
Add colored miniature marshmallows on top and melt them, if desired.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Wash and sort cranberries.
Peel orange.
Grind all together (I use my food processor).
Add sugar.
I start with a cup of sugar and add more if it needs it.

title: special sweet and sour sauce
directions: Chop the Chinese greens, bean sprouts, green onions, water chestnuts, carrots and mushrooms. Saute the vegetables in cooking oil; do not overcook.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Add in remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Bake 3 layers 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the day before serving and refrigerate overnight in casserole dish.
Take out 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat broiler, heat a charcoal grill until coals form white ash, or preheat gas grill to medium.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of hot water.
Blend in cranberry sauce.
Add mandarin oranges (drained) and pineapple with juice and nuts (optional).

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a large heavy saucepan and mix well. Gradually add water and lemon juice, stirring until mixture is smooth.

title: corn souffle
directions: Melt butter and flour, gradually add milk.
When well cooked add corn and well beaten egg yolks.
Add salt and pepper, sugar to taste.
Fold in egg whites which have been beaten to semi-stiff peaks.
Put in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: frito salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except last two ingredients.
Mix those in immediately before serving.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice according to the directions on package.
Pull or chop cooked chicken.
Mix soup, mushrooms, onion, mayo, water chestnuts and water. Then add cooked wild rice and chicken.
Put in large casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cake icing
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and milk.
Remove from fire and pour in 1 box of powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Mix, then spread on cake.

title: fancy mashed sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place sweet potatoes in a bowl.
Add pineapple, juice, butter and spices; blend together.
Mix in nuts and pour into oiled baking dish.
Top with marshmallows and bake for about 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: arabic plain rice
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan.
Rinse rice in cold water, drain and add to butter.
Saute for a few minutes.
Add boiling water and salt.
Cover, lower heat and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Rice is done when all water is absorbed and kernels are flaky.
Serves 4.

title: pepsi cola cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, and chopped nuts in a bowl; set aside.
In a small pan, mix butter, cocoa and Pepsi.
Bring to boil, then pour over flour mixture.
Beat well.
Add eggs, soda, mini marshmallows, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour into greased 8 x 11 pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: broccoli with wine sauce
directions: Combine mayonnaise, wine, lemon juice and curry powder in saucepan. Cook over low heat, until warm and mixed well; do not boil. Cook broccoli for 10 minutes. Serve sauce over broccoli and garnish with pimento strips.

title: brownies
directions: Mix butter and sugar, add eggs and beat.
Combine with cocoa and add flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Blend all ingredients. Pour into pie shells. Freeze. Set out 15 minutes before serving.

title: southern spoon bread(cornbread)
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 40 minutes or until nice and brown.

title: hattie's potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes into large chunks.
Cook until done. Drain and cool to lukewarm water.
Boil eggs to hard-boiled.
Peel and chop eggs.
Put all ingredients into a large bowl.
With both hands, mix all ingredients.
Squeeze potatoes until partially mashed and part are small chunks.
Chill before serving.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and cool in refrigerator before eating it.

title: grandma phyl's apple cheese bake
directions: Place apples in a greased 9-inch square pan. Combine water and lemon; pour over the apples. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix together the sugar, flour and salt. Cut in oleo to form a crumbly crust. Add cheese and mix lightly.
Spread over the apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until apples are tender and topping is lightly browned.

title: cherry-cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add cranberry sauce. Stir until smooth.
Refrigerate until cool. Add nuts and pineapple. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or until firm.
Serves 6.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients and drain excess grease.
Add the remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Line bottom of casserole dish with tortilla chips.
Add a layer of the mixture.
Alternate layers of tortilla chips with layers of mixture, but have a layer of tortilla chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and continue cooking until cheese melts.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; add cheese and mix well.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, milk and butter; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
May also make as bread; pour into greased loaf pans.

title: cheery cherry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and form into balls or a loaf.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over meat. Cook 1 hour at 300°, covered, and then 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: what-ya-ma-call-it-salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, potatoes, margarine and cinnamon in a large bowl, stirring well.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well; add to first ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling two-thirds full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields about 1 1/3 dozen muffins.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut corn from cob, then scrape cob for milk left in cob.
Melt butter in skillet, add corn and cook over medium heat for ten minutes, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper, and sugar and cook five minutes.
Stir in cream or evaporated milk and serve.

title: western bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef until crumbly.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except beans.
Mix well.
Add beans.
Mix, taking care not to mash up beans.
Place in a
1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: This recipe is to be made in two stages.
One day before serving, mix the first six ingredients together and chill overnight.

title: moist pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients, adding eggs one at a time.
Sift together next 5 ingredients; set aside.
Measure water and pumpkin.
To the creamed mixture, add a small amount of dry ingredients.
(For variety, add 1/2 cup chopped walnuts, 1 cup chopped dates, 1 cup raisins or 1 cup coconut.)
Bake in 2 greased, not floured, loaf pans at 325°.
Serve, while warm, topped with Cool Whip or ice lightly.
Can be served at breakfast, by toasting, and topped with jelly.

title: blond brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter; add sugar and stir until it has dissolved.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder together; add that with vanilla to the batter.
Coat chocolate bits and nuts lightly with flour, then fold into cake dough. Butter a 9 x 12 1/2-inch pan and dust with flour.
Bake brownies for 30 minutes and leave pan in oven for another 15 minutes.
Cut in squares while still warm.
These keep well if wrapped in foil once they are cooled.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Grate all vegetables, except tomatoes (may be shredded finely if prefer).
Place in very large kettle.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, bay leaves, marjoram, paprika, thyme and water to cover; spread hamburger on top.
Bring to boiling on high.
Stir well. Reduce heat and simmer about 1 hour.
Add peas, corn and green beans; cook about 25 minutes.
Herbs can be adjusted to suit your family preference.

title: southwestern artichoke dip
directions: Drain and finely chop artichoke hearts.
Blend together all ingredients using only 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Reserve remaining 1/4 cup to spread on top before baking.

title: eight can soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Place in crockpot or soup pot. Mix remaining ingredients (do not drain them) adding to the pot. Simmer all day on low or get mixture real hot and then simmer several hours.
Leftovers can be frozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix in order given one ingredient at a time.
Beat well. Shape, press with fork and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Cook pudding per package directions.
Use milk and juice as cooking liquid.
Cool.
Save 1 tablespoon raisins for garnish. Stir remaining raisins and 3/4 carton whipped topping into pudding.
Measure and drain 1/2 cup pineapple for garnish.
Cut cake into chunks.
Pour 1 cup pudding mixture into 3-quart glass bowl.
Top with half of each: cake, jam, remaining undrained pineapple, undrained tropical fruit and pudding.
Repeat layers. Chill 20 minutes or overnight.
Spoon remaining whipped topping over trifle.
Garnish with reserved pineapple, raisins, almonds and raspberries.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli toss
directions: Mix the cream cheese, vinegar, sugar, mustard, pepper, garlic powder, egg and oil in blender.
Combine the last 4 ingredients. Add dressing just before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix well the flour, sugar and salt. Add milk.
Cook on medium heat. I like to put in a little cream cheese as it thickens. Slowly pour in egg yolks. Add vanilla. Let cool. Use bananas. Top with Cool Whip.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together very well and bake at 350° until golden brown on top, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix together oil and liquids until creamy.
Add to flour and salt.
Mix with fork.
Roll out between wax paper.
Makes two 9-inch shells.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling in the bottom of an oblong glass baking dish, next add crushed pineapple, spreading out over the cherries, next add the dry cake mix over the fruit, then the pecans, slice the butter and place over the pecans, covering the whole top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 - 40 min. or until golden on top.
Serve with ice cream.

title: round cheese bread
directions: In a bowl, combine the first six ingredients (batter will be thick). Spoon into greased 8 inch round baking pan. Drizzle with butter; sprinkle with additional parmesan cheese if desired. Bake at 400° for 20 - 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes. Cut into wedges. Serve warm.

title: shrimp mold 1
directions: Dissolve
unflavored gelatin in cold water over low heat. In medium bowl add
Kraft Thousand Island dressing to softened cream cheese. Stir in fresh lemon juice,
salt and gelatin to dressing and cream cheese mixture. Add chopped, cooked shrimp and celery. Pour into mold pan and chill until firm.

title: hamburger roll-up
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients to form a stiff dough and roll into a rectangle.
Mix hamburger, water and salt; sprinkle on a little flour so mixture will stick together.
Now spread hamburger mixture over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Mix next 7 ingredients and simmer for about 35 minutes.
Now transfer this mixture to a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Then lay hamburger roll on top and add the 1 pint water.
Bake in a slow oven for about 30 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except Cheddar cheese.
Let bubble a few minutes.
Pour beef and vegetable mixture into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake, covered, 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and milk.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Take out and roll the size desired.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook macaroni and drain good.
Layer macaroni and cheese.
Then, pour mixture of egg and milk over this and let stand 2 hours.
Cook at 350° until set, about 30 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Mix
milk, sugar and margarine and bring to boil over medium heat.
When it bubbles all over, a low heat start, start timing. Boil 8 minutes.
Take off heat and stir in chocolate chips until melted; then add marshmallow cream.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour out on greased pans.

title: texas-style chuck roast
directions: In large skillet, brown roast on both sides in hot oil over medium-high flame.
Remove roast to a 3-quart shallow casserole. Add garlic and onion to skillet; reduce flame to medium-low and saute until onion is soft.
Add undrained pineapple and tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, mustard, peppers and salt.
Stir to blend. Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over roast.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° gas oven 1 hour.
Remove foil; bake 30 minutes longer or until beef is tender.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine and mix thoroughly 1 1/2 minutes in microwave.
Put in large bowl the sugar and Rice Krispies.
Mix together.
Pour peanut butter mixture over Rice Krispies mixture and mix thoroughly.
Form into 1-inch balls and chill overnight.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Place tabouli mix into a bowl.
Add all ingredients except lettuce.
Refrigerate 1/2 to 1 hour to absorb water and blend flavors.
Serve on bed of lettuce with fresh parsley, radishes, etc., as garnish.

title: shelia's chili sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Simmer until thick.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Seal immediately.

title: quick vidalia bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pan or muffin tins.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and let stand in refrigerator until firm.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar with water and Karo.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking until very hard, brittle ball is formed or a thread spins (275° or 280° on candy thermometer).
Remove from fire.
Add syrup gradually to 2 stiffly beaten egg whites beaten until stiff but not dry. Turn to medium speed and continue beating until stiff.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: broccoli mushroom chowder
directions: Cut broccoli into 1/2-inch pieces.
Steam in 1/2 cup water until tender; do not drain.
Set aside.
Melt butter in large pot and add flour to make a roux.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken stock, stirring with wire whisk and bring to boil.
Turn heat to low. Add broccoli, sliced mushrooms, half and half, spices and cheese. Heat, but do not boil.

title: barbecue sauce (microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High in microwave for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Let stand several minutes. Serve with ribs, chicken, chops and hamburgers.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes 1/8-inch thick.
Put half in crock-pot.
Add half of soup, half of ham and half of onion.
Put other half of potatoes, soup, ham and onion.
Pour milk over top.
Stir slightly. Cook on low for 8 to 9 hours or on high 4 to 5. Can add 1/2 cup grated cheese before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Mix and let stand until warm the yeast packets, flour, warm water and eggs.
Add to first mixture and beat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add 3 1/2 to 4 cups flour. Knead until smooth (leave dough moist; will feel slightly sticky). Put in buttered bowl and butter top of mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 1 1/2 hours.
(Roll out dough; cut and fold over.
Brush with melted butter.
Cover and let rise 2 hours.) Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: center ring punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine punch and pineapple juice; mix well.
Add cherry soda.
Unmold and float fruited ice ring on surface.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix all
ingredients
well and chill.
Serve with chips or also good with fresh vegetables.

title: best ever dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange pineapple chunks over cherries.
Sprinkle with the cake mix.
Cover with melted margarine and top with coconut and pecans or walnuts.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Serve warm with ice cream or may be served cold.

title: anth's pull aparts
directions: You will need 1 pie plate and 1 glass cup.

title: apple-celery salad
directions: Chop apples and celery.
Combine all ingredients.

title: aunti vi's cake
directions: Bake cake as directed, using pineapple juice instead of water. Cool!
Mix cream cheese with milk and blend with pudding for 2 minutes.
After cake is cool, spread with cream cheese mixture. Cover with crushed pineapple, then spread with Cool Whip.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12.

title: scrambled eggs with sour cream
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
In a bowl, gently beat eggs and blend in sour cream and seasonings.
Put egg mixture in skillet and cook to desired firmness.
Serves 4.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook over moderate heat until well blended.
Add the milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Serve warm over ice cream.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Sift flour, soda, salt and sugar together into a large bowl.
Add butter.
With a pastry blender or two knives cut in the butter until the mixture looks like coarse meal. Stir in raisins and caraway seed.
Add milk gradually.
Mix until well blended.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead about 1 minute.
Cut dough in half.
Shape each half into a round ball.
Place on a greased cookie sheet. Flatten the balls slightly with the hand.
With a knife, make a shallow cross on the top of each ball.
Bake about 1 hour, until well browned.
Cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well except potatoes and put into casserole dish.
Put diced potatoes on top.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender and begin to brown.

title: cobblers
directions: Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Melt margarine in dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Batter will be thin.
Pour over margarine in dish.
Add fruit.
Spoon over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: meatball and potato casserole
directions: Quarter potatoes; add 1/2 teaspoon salt and set aside. Combine beef, bread crumbs, milk, onion and seasoning.
Mix well; shape into egg-shaped balls.
Roll into flour.
Fry until brown in oil.
Add 2 cups of water.
Place potatoes in pan with meat. Cover and simmer for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: coconut sweet potatoes
directions: Can substitute orange juice for rum.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan or glass baking dish with Pam.
Put coconut and pecans on the bottom.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to the box.
Pour over the nuts and coconut.
Melt cream cheese and margarine together.
Stir in powdered sugar.
Pour over the cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Grease	pan
x
13-inch).
Put coconut on bottom of pan. Mix Swiss chocolate cake mix by directions and pour over coconut. Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Put this
mixture in globs on cake and swirl.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: skinny hoppin' john
directions: Rinse the peas and place them in a deep saucepan with 2 1/2 cups cold water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a simmer. Cook until peas are almost soft, about an hour. Stir in tomatoes, scallions, celery, onion, chili pepper and salt. Simmer 25 minutes over medium heat. Mix in lime juice and season to taste with pepper.

title: deep dish pizza pie
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and mushrooms with ground beef. Pour off any fat.
Take off heat.
Stir in tomato sauce, then slightly beaten egg, seasonings and spices.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Top with cheeses.

title: vegetable manicotti(serves 6)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with Pam. Combine Ricotta, egg whites, Parmesan, Italian seasoning and salt. Fill each manicotti with cheese mixture.
Top with vegetables. Cover with combined sauce and wine.
Cover dish with foil and bake 40 minutes or until pasta is tender.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: peach-glazed cornish hen with ginger
directions: Place hens skin side up in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and broil 6 inches from heat, 3 to 5 minutes or until skin is lightly browned.
Combine peaches and remaining ingredients in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour sauce over hens.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: hawaiian chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate chicken for up to 3 days. Works best for chicken with bones.

title: jello salad
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk in top of double boiler.
Pour hot mixture over Jell-O in large bowl.
Stir until Jell-O is dissolved, then stir in cream cheese (cheese may be softened in microwave) until cheese dissolves.
Then add pineapple with juice. Cool slightly and blend in mayonnaise and whipping cream.
Chill overnight or until firm.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole #2
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower until tender.
While this is cooking, saute chopped onion in margarine.
Add milk to sauteed onion and also add Velveeta cheese to make cheese sauce.
Drain vegetables.
Mix in beaten eggs and pour cheese sauce on vegetables.

title: drip beef
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Place roast and seasonings in a large crock-pot.
Cover and simmer for eight hours.
Add water while cooking if needed.
Remove fat and bone.
Stir until meat falls apart.
Serve on French rolls with "horsey sauce" (horseradish) and dip in broth from meat.

title: cafe vienna mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift and stir in the remaining ingredients.
Roll in balls, walnut size, and roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: veggie wedgies
directions: For crust, unroll crescent rolls.
Pat into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch ungreased baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool completely.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together cream cheese, sour cream and dressing mix until smooth.
Spread on top of cooled crust.
Top with chopped or sliced mixed vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese over vegetables.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
(Great for an appetizer or at a picnic!)
Serves 35.

title: chocoroons
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes, or until light golden brown.

title: potato and cabbage soup
directions: In a large soup kettle, saute onion in butter until tender. Add water, cabbage, potatoes, bouillon cubes, pepper and garlic. Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir in ham.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli or spinach and layer in casserole with mushrooms and dressing and mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: spoon bread
directions: Add hot water to corn meal, then shortening, sugar and salt. When well mixed, add milk and well beaten eggs.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a moderate oven at 375°.

title: mrs. frank reynold's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa together.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in vanilla and milk.
Add melted margarine, then coconut.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes, or until firm.
A cup of nuts for each pie may be added, if desired.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Add eggs to first 4 ingredients.
Stir and blend flour, soda, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla.
Mix with butter and egg mixture.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until light brown.
Do not overcook.
Let stand on cookie sheet a few minutes before removing.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix preceding ingredients well; pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.
Cool before cutting.

title: bacon, chicken
directions: Dice cauliflower into "hash brown" sized pieces and set aside.
Cut bacon crossways in 1/2-inch pieces; saut until almost crisp.
Add onion and continue simmering a few minutes. Add chicken.
Heat through.
Place in bowl with slotted spoon, reserving a tablespoon of bacon drippings in skillet.

title: hungary-cold cherry soup
directions: Empty the can into a strainer over a pan.
Push the cherries through the strainer (mash them in a blender first if this is difficult).
Add the water and cook over a medium heat until the mixture starts to boil.
Mix the cornstarch and sugar with a little water.
Add this to the soup.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring all the time.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into a bowl and chill in the refrigerator.
Serve with a spoonful of cream and a few mint leaves.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients
except
cup of nuts.
Chill and shape into a ball.	Roll
ball in the other cup of chopped nuts.

title: wild rice with scallions and cranberries
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, heat olive oil. Add onion and garlic. Cook until tender. Add wild rice, salt and pepper; stir.
Add chicken stock; bring to boil. Reduce heat to simmer; cook until rice is tender (30 to 60 minutes). If all liquid is not absorbed but rice is tender, strain off liquid.

title: chocolate chip and cream cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and sugar until blended well.
Cut 1 roll of cookie dough into 1/2-inch slices; line the bottom of the pan.
Pour the cheese mixture over the slices, then cut the second roll into 1/2-inch slices and place on top of the mixture.
Do not push down.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until brown.
Slice when cool.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Cook for 5 minutes. Set aside and add margarine.

title: peppermint fudge cake
directions: This recipe for cake will be appreciated by mothers.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients. Spread evenly over the bottom of a glass 9-inch baking dish or pie dish. Sprinkle a layer of tomatoes over the bean mixture.
Sprinkle a layer of cheese over all.
Let set in refrigerator from 2 to 24 hours. Serve with taco chips.

title: pickled squash
directions: Combine squash and onions in a large container.
Cover with ice and salt; set aside for 1 hour.
Put bell peppers on ice the last 5 minutes of the hour.
Drain and rinse well.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices; bring to a boil.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until done. Mash. Add salt, pepper, cheese, egg, margarine, milk and cracker crumbs. Combine well. Pour in casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Meanwhile, press biscuits into 12-inch round greased pizza pan, pinching edges of biscuits together to seal.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix with uncooked rice, Cheez Whiz and soup, undiluted.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: easy cinnamon logs
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then roll into shape of logs. Roll each log in sugar/cinnamon mixture. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: wok the chicken!
directions: Sprinkle chicken with cornstarch.
Turn wok to high heat.
Add oil.
Add chicken.
Toss about 3 to 5 minutes.
Add green pepper and mushrooms, toss about 2 minutes more.
Add sugar and oyster sauce. Mix.
Add broth at end.
Serve with or over rice.
Prep time:
10 minutes.
Cook time:
8 minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush cookies fine.
Melt butter and add cookies, except 1/4 cup for top.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cream cheese, Cool Whip and then pudding.
Repeat Cool Whip and pudding. Place 1/4 cup on top.

title: mock turkey
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 45 minutes.

title: candied carrots
directions: Slice carrots.
Cook in enough water to cover until tender. Add other ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into deep pan.
Add about 1 cup of water. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Combine the melted oleo, flour, brown sugar and oatmeal.
Put this mixture on top of apples and bake until brown.

title: strawberry dream pie
directions: Combine pudding, gelatin, water and lemon juice.
Cook until mixture boils.
Then cool.
Fold whipped topping into cooled gelatin mixture.
Stir in strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell. Garnish with whipped topping and strawberries.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Scrub cukes. Do not peel. In 5-quart bowl, sprinkle salt over cukes, onion and pepper. Stir gently. Let stand with foil on, 1 to 3 hours or overnight. If overnight, place in refrigerator. Drain off liquid. Combine vinegar, sugar and seeds. Pour over cuke/onion/pepper. Stir and cover. Let stand 36 hours in refrigerator. Store, covered, in refrigerator. Makes 1 1/2 quarts or 6 cups.

title: smoked salmon log
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Flake the fish.
Combine cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt and flaked fish.
Mix thoroughly.
Place mixture on wax paper and shape into a log.
Chill for several hours.
Combine pecans and parsley. Roll salmon log in parsley-nut mixture.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: krissy's bourbon balls
directions: Melt
chocolate
and butter in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add
remaining
ingredients.
If too wet, add more oatmeal. If too dry, add more bourbon.
Roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Let stand overnight at room temperature.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix together Cheddar cheese and Monterey Jack cheese after shredding.
Cook noodles until tender; drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef in large skillet with onion.
Drain excess grease.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer noodles, ground beef and cheeses.
Make another layer the same, this time add the cottage cheese before the ground beef.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate hazelnut pudding(nohr im hend)
directions: Whip together butter and powdered sugar.
Moisten diced white bread with milk.
Add diced bread and chocolate heated gently until liquid to butter mix.
Whip egg whites and granulated sugar to an oily consistency; carefully fold the whisked egg whites into the mixture.
Stir in flour, bread crumbs and grated hazelnuts.

title: fried collard greens
directions: Cut up greens to desired cut.
Wash greens.
Do not drain. Heat bacon drippings in boiler that you would cook greens in until hot.
Put greens in boiler.
Stir, then cover.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir every once in a while until done.

title: cucumber sauce
directions: Drain
excess juice from cucumbers.
Place in a bowl and add dill
weed,
sugar, salt, pepper and lemon juice; mix well. Fold in sour cream and chill thoroughly.
Great on boiled fish, baked potatoes or as
dip for your favorite crackers.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Mix vegetables, soup, 1/2 package cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can onion rings.
Put in 2-quart baking dish (sprayed with Pam).
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add the rest of the cheese and onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine hot roll mix, yeast packet (in box) and sugar; mix well.
Stir in hot water, margarine and egg until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface. With greased or floured hands, shape dough into a ball.
Knead dough for 5 minutes, until smooth.
Sprinkle additional flour over surface to reduce stickiness.
Cover dough with large bowl; let rest for 5 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Simmer garlic and onion in a little olive oil; add sliced zucchini.
Cook until tender.
Add 1 can tomatoes or some sliced or diced fresh ones.
Season with salt, pepper and a little basil. Top with mozzarella cheese.
This can be done in skillet or placed in baking dish and placed in oven at 350° until cheese melts, approximately 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix zucchini, oil, eggs and nuts in blender.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and the zucchini mixture.
Pour into 2 greased bread baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise, salad dressing, salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over cabbage.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: chile egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs, add remaining ingredients except chilies.
Fold in chilies.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cooked all the way through.
Serve hot. Makes 10 to 12 servings.
You may substitute bacon with breakfast sausage or smokey links that have been cooked and cut into bite size pieces.

title: cheese and bacon quiche
directions: Fry bacon and drain excess oil.
Add onions.
Fry until tender.
Pour
into
pie
shell.
Mix eggs, milk, Bisquick and seasonings in bowl.
Pour over onions and bacon.
Grate cheese and sprinkle on top of pie.
Garnish with broccoli flowerets. Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gwynn's beans
directions: Brown and scramble beef and sausage until done.
Add bell pepper and onion; cook until tender.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a casserole dish or pan and bake until bubbly hot.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush wafers and add powdered sugar and melted butter. Add orange juice (full strength) and pecans. Make into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: potato boats
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Dry on paper towel and rub skins with Crisco. Bake potatoes until done.
Remove from oven and cut into lengthwise.
Scoop out potato.
Save potato skins.
Mash potato with the onion, Cheez Whiz, oleo, salt and pepper.
Add enough milk to make potatoes fluffy.
Scoop potato mixture back into potato skins.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a pan and boil.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Add oats and vanilla.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Let cool at room temperature. Makes about 24 cookies.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: You will also need 20 to 24 wooden sticks.

title: golden chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch), arrange chicken, skin side down.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: creamy sweet potato pies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in 2 Pet pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until set.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 450° for 45 minutes or until fork-tender. Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut a thin slice off top of each potato. Carefully scoop out potato insides; reserve shells.
In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat potatoes and margarine until creamy.
Gradually beat in milk, garlic powder and black pepper.
Stir in broccoli and red pepper.
Spoon mixture into shells.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: In large, shallow dish or self-sealing plastic bag, combine lemon juice, water, oil, rosemary, garlic and bouillon.
Mix well. Add steak; cover dish or seal bag.
Marinate 6 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Prepare outdoor grill for cooking.
Remove meat from marinade.
Transfer marinade to small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute and set aside.
Place steak on grill.
Grill 15 minutes, basting frequently with marinade.
To serve, slice steak thinly and accompany with fettuccine and green beans.
Yields 5 servings (per serving 475 calories, 18 g fat).

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and butter and add to boiling water slowly, beating until smooth over heat.
Remove from heat; add baking powder to eggs and combine with milk.
Add to cornmeal mixture, stirring well.
Turn into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot fudge sundae topping
directions: In top of double boiler, over simmering water, melt, until smooth, the milk chocolate morsels.
Add Eagle Brand milk, Karo syrup, butter or margarine, stirring often.
When smooth, cook, without stirring, for 30 minutes over hot water.
Put through blender until smooth.
Makes 1 quart.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until thick; add a pinch of salt. Add cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Add 1 small jar pimentos and 2 or 3 sweet pickles, cut up fine.

title: kung pao krunch
directions: In a large bowl, combine popped corn with chow mein noodles and peanuts. Set aside.
