In medium saucepan over medium heat, bring corn syrup to a boil. Boil rapidly 7 minutes; remove from heat. Working quickly, stir in remaining ingredients; pour over popped corn mixture, tossing gently to coat. Evenly spread coated corn onto greased wax paper.
Using two forks, pull popcorn mixture as thinly as possible. Allow to cool before breaking into smaller pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 quart.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Do not overcook.
When they cook, they will get hard, but are crisp, crunchy and delicious with coffee.

title: fried apple rings
directions: Core the apples and slice 1/3-inch thick.
Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add apples.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, honey and salt.
Fry on medium heat until golden brown.
Turn and fry on other side.

title: brown soda bread
directions: Put all-purpose flour in bowl; add salt and baking soda and stir together with fork.
Add whole wheat flour and mix.
Blend butter into flour mixture with pastry blender.
Make a well in center and add buttermilk; stir until blended (dough should be dry enough to knead, but not too dry).
Knead on floured board about 30 seconds.
Pat into greased 8-inch pan (black frying pan).
Cut gashes to form a cross.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for about 30 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes a small loaf.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Soak chicken wings in hot salt water for about an hour or until thawed.
Drain; spread on cookie sheets and sprinkle well with Season-All salt.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Drain juice off cookie sheets, cover liberally with barbecue sauce.
Broil until done to your taste.
Dump into crock-pot on low heat.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Use warm water from tap.
Put in bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over water and let dissolve.
Mix oil and honey in yeast mixture and salt.
Mix well.
Add milk (can use powdered milk and warm water). Add flour 2 or 3 cups at a time and mix well.
You may need more or less.
Knead for a while and let stand in bowl covered with a damp cloth until double in size.
Punch down and make rolls or loaf and let rise again until almost double in size. Then bake at 350° to 400° approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Melt butter and mix with flour. Add mushroom soup and stir until thick. Add crabmeat, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and cheese. Put in oil-sprayed dish and cook in 350° oven until hot and slightly brown.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Cook the noodles in boiling water and drain. Add the remaining ingredients.
Put all together in a 2-quart casserole. Top with about 3/4 cup buttered crumbs.
Bake about 45 minutes or until done.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine last 6 ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Heat all ingredients to boiling then simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot sterile jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: italian beef
directions: Place roast in a heavy roaster or chicken fryer. Mix all ingredients and pour over roast. Bake 3 to 4 hours at 325°. Remove roast to cutting board. Allow meat to cool enough to handle. Slice thinly and return to the broth. Serve on steak buns.

title: bacon cheddar puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring milk and margarine to boil over medium heat.
Add flour, all at once, stirring constantly until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased, foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Wrap securely; freeze.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in a glass bowl.
In a saucepan, put sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Pour over vegetables and marinate overnight.
Keeps in refrigerator for two weeks very well.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: skillet cake
directions: Grease skillet and heat in oven while mixing all ingredients together.
Pour into skillet as you would cornbread and bake at 350° until done.
Top with strawberries for shortcake or hot fudge for hot fudge cake.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: In large saucepan, bring sugar, butter, milk and cocoa to a boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Stir for a few minutes to cool slightly.
Add oats and peanuts.
Drop mixture by tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Let cool and harden.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bone and cut up chicken.
Mix with broth, soup, vegetables and pepper and put in bottom of baking dish.
Mix flour, buttermilk, oleo and pepper and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix well and pour in graham shell.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
After cooling, add your favorite fruit topping to it.

title: prune nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Add dry ingredients and then add the yogurt, diced prunes, lemon peel and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pork loin with jezebel sauce
directions: Stir together hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce; set aside. Combine garlic salt and pepper.
Place pork in a lightly greased roasting pan.
Brush all sides of pork loin with sauce mixture; sprinkle with garlic salt mixture.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours or until a meat thermometer inserted in thickest portion registers 160°, shielding with aluminum foil the last 30 minutes.
Let stand, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Serve with Jezebel sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: claw sandwiches
directions: Take breadsticks out and straighten them out.
Cut each one in half.
Cut 2 slits in one end of each of them.
Spread out to look like claw.
Bake as directed.

title: peanut butter cups (reese's)
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate chips and pour over the mixture.
Chill. Cut into 60 pieces while still warm.

title: skoby's corn
directions: Mix and simmer 20 minutes, stirring constantly. Sprinkle with Stovetop stuffing mix. Serve.

title: orange cream cake
directions: Combine and beat on medium speed for 2 minutes: lemon cake mix, Kool-Aid, eggs, warm water and oil.
Pour in ungreased 13 x 9 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Using a meat fork, poke holes in cake.
Cool on rack for 30 minutes.
Dissolve package orange Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; add 1 cup cold water.
Pour over cake.
Cool and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: standard waffles
directions: Sift flour. Measure and add baking powder and salt. Separate yolks and whites of eggs and beat
each well. Combine egg yolks, milk and butter. Add flour gradually, beating until smooth. Fold in egg whites. Makes 6 waffles.

title: watergate salad
directions: Do not drain pineapple.
Thaw Cool Whip.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put in buttered square or oblong container and freeze.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Let stand for 1 hour. Mix together remaining ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Pour over squash mixture and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: garlic cheddar biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine biscuit mix, cheese and onion. Stir in milk until a soft dough forms. Stir 30 seconds longer. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sour cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs, then sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned around edge (center will be slightly soft).
Cool.
Chill.
Top with cherry filling.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: dianes pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients together in large bowl; pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° bake for 40 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all in 2-quart saucepan and cook 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven.

title: walter mack's famous beer batter
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, fold in 2 egg whites. Batter should be consistency of pancake batter.
If too thin, add more flour.
If too thick add more beer.
Use to batter fish, chicken, broccoli, etc., for frying.
(Walter's Beer Batter is famous on our campus.)

title: no fat vegetable dip or sauce(serves 4)
directions: Blend ingredients.
Serve warm over cooked vegetables (e.g. baked potatoes, broccoli or use as a veggie dip for carrot sticks, celery, cauliflower, etc.)

title: lite fluffy dessert
directions: Blend all together.
Fold in crushed pineapple (drained). Chill.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.
Yield: 6 dozen

title: red onion potato salad(thanks to ann tyrell)
directions: Boil potatoes in skins, peel and slice while hot.
Place potatoes in large bowl; add Italian dressing, mix well and chill.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat thoroughly.
Sift together the flour and dry ingredients except baking soda.
Dissolve soda in applesauce. Add flour mixture alternately with applesauce mixture to sugar, shortening and egg.
Fold in nut meats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks.
Mix together dry ingredients. Add milk.
Add vanilla and nuts. Fold in egg whites. Bake in loaf pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter chocolate pie
directions: Spread peanut butter in warm pie crust. Spread Jell-O over peanut butter filling. Top with Cool Whip. Yummy!! So easy.
Can do ahead.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese. Cook until thick.
Scoop on hamburger rolls.
Add a slice of cheese.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Melt margarine and Crisco; pour into dry ingredients.
Add eggs and mix well. Add pecans (finely chopped) and mix with hands.
Pinch off small portions (or use spoon).
Roll into ball the size of large marbles and put on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: veal jason
directions: Blend together, heat and keep warm.

title: jumbo shells with meat
directions: Cook shells half done; drain water.
In large bowl, mix salt, pepper, 1/2 can Parmesan cheese, Ricotta cheese, garlic, parsley and seasoned salt together.
Brown ground beef, onion and mushrooms; drain excess fat and mix with other.
Add egg.
Take 3 tablespoons spaghetti sauce and put in bottom of baking pan.
Fill shells with meat sauce; place in pan after all shells are filled. Top with spaghetti sauce; sprinkle with other half of Parmesan cheese and 2 cups of Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil; bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: sarah's bread and butter pickles *
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, pepper, garlic and salt.
Mix well. Cover with ice cubes, let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Drain.
Mix spices, vinegar and sugar; pour over pickles and let come to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Place in jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute onions, peppers and garlic until onions are slightly cooked.
Add all ingredients except parsley.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes until vegetables are tender but crisp.
Stir in parsley, cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve hot or cold.

title: washpot chicken stew
directions: Build fire using hickory or oak wood under and around washpot.
Fry fatback until crisp and remove from pot, leaving grease for seasoning.
Add water, chicken, onions and gizzards. Use hot fire.
Boil and frequently stir 30 minutes before adding all other ingredients, except livers.
Remove bones when meat has separated from them.
Continue to boil another 20 to 30 minutes until gizzards are tender.
Move most of fire away from washpot and add livers to stew.
Livers should be thoroughly cooked after simmering about 15 minutes.
Remove all fire from washpot and serve a delicious stew.
Serve with saltine crackers.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Stir in sugar and let set 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover bowl tightly.
Chill at least 24 hours.
Chopped pimento adds color if you wish.

title: rice krispie peanut squares
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Add peanut butter; bring to boil.
Pour over Rice Krispies and press into buttered pan.
Cut into squares immediately and let set until firm.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: night before cinnamon rolls
directions: Evening: Mix brown sugar and cream. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dot with margarine. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts. Place frozen dough balls evenly over mixture. Refrigerate.

title: new england clam boil
directions: Layer in real big pan the clam juice and steamers (if you have them), potatoes, link sausages, hot dogs, onions, corn, *crab legs, shrimp or lobster, clams (heated in separate pan when clam boil is finished) and melted butter.
When everything is layered, put on tightly closed lid.
Turn on low heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve with fresh Italian bread.

title: busy day stroganoff
directions: Cut steaks into strips.
Brown in oil with onions.
Cook until tender.
Add mushrooms with liquid.
Add soup and garlic pepper. Cook over medium heat for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
When meat is tender, add sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: tres leches dominicano
directions: Following directions on the white cake mix box, bake a cake. Cool completely. Run knife around edges of pan. Using a knife, remove the golden top crust from cake and divide it in small parts with a knife. Make sure to run a knife all the way down on pan as you divide it.

title: bubble bread
directions: * Pull biscuits apart and cut each into 4 pieces.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix first three ingredients well and let stand overnight. Drain, rinse and drain well.
Put all ingredients in large kettle and boil 20 minutes.
Stir often.
Makes 7 pints.
Seal in hot sterile jars.

title: pie crust for frying
directions: Use for crisp fried pies and burritos.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, egg and salt together; then add milk, flour and baking powder.
Beat well; to this add cocoa that has been melted in butter.
Beat well; add vanilla, hot water and baking soda.
The batter will be thin, but this is a quick easy recipe.
Bake in moderate oven until done.

title: meatballs and noodles
directions: Roll meat into balls and brown.
In saucepan, mix tomato paste, tomato sauce, spaghetti mix and mushrooms (follow water directions on pack).
Place meatballs in saucepan; let simmer for 20 minutes. Use fun noodles (curly and spiral noodles).
Serves 4.

title: garlic-cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, garlic and shortening.
Add cheese and buttermilk. Roll out like biscuits.
Bake at 500° until desired brownish.

title: ritz cracker chicken
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry. Melt margarine and add garlic salt. Roll chicken in margarine mixture and dip into crumbs.
Place in ungreased pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: no fat spaghetti sauce
directions: Add 1/2 cup water to saucepan.
Chop onion and garlic.
Add and simmer.
Add all seasoning.
When onions are soft, add 2 cans tomato paste and 2 cans water.
Simmer.
Add crushed tomatoes, cook about 1 hour on low heat.
You can add salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and cool whip.
In a large bowl, layer nilla wafers on bottom, adding the pudding mixture and sliced bananas.
Continue layering starting with wafers.
Garnish with bananas and wafers.
Chill over night for best results.

title: a variation of ma's best spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Combine meat loaf mix, bread crumbs, grated cheese and milk.
Mix in eggs, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Roll into 2-inch meatballs.
Cook 20 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: avocado sauce for fish and poultry
directions: Peel and put avocado; place in a food processor or blender. Add lime, spices and garlic.
Process until smooth.
Serve with poached fish, grilled chicken or steamed prawns.
Yields about 1 1/4 cups.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Add first 5 ingredients and cook until you hear the peanuts pop or separate.
Add soda. Stir fast, then pour in buttered pie pan or long tin pan.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in oven for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, crushed pineapple, celery seed, parsley, garlic salt, onion and green pepper.
Form into ball or log and roll in crushed pecans or more green parsley.
Refrigerate until firm and serve with assorted crackers.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding beaten egg whites last.
Fry in deep fat, using a wire basket as for doughnuts.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, seasoning mix and 1/2 bottle of taco sauce.
Spread on round plate.
Top with rest of sauce, then top with chopped lettuce, tomato and grated cheese.
Serve with Doritos.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix
together
flour and salt.
Cut in shortening, then oleo. Mix together egg, vinegar and water.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an oblong pan (13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch).
Melt chocolate and shortening over low heat.
Beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Measure flour by sifting.
Stir flour, salt and baking powder together; blend in.
Mix in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until brownies pull away from sides of pan.
Do not overbake.
Cool slightly and cut in bars.

title: teriyaki beef
directions: Taste sauce.
If too sweet, add soy sauce; if too salty, add a little water.
Soak meat overnight.
Fry in a pan alone or with peppers and onions.
You can cook it on the grill or stir-fry it with your favorite vegetables and serve with rice.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Plunge tomatoes into boiling water to loosen skin.
Drain, peel, cut into small pieces and cook over medium heat.
Slow cooking improves flavor.
Season with salt, pepper and butter.
A small onion may be cooked with tomatoes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix oil and seasonings.
Pour over drained beans, green peppers and onions.
Let stand overnight and serve.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: turnip greens
directions: Wash and
prepare
greens;
pre-boil
until
tender
by adding 1/2 teaspoon
soda.
Drain all liquid from greens.
Put into frying pan; add bouillon cubes, salt and oil.
Put lid on pan. Let simmer 30 minutes on low heat.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Combine rice, blueberries and 3 tablespoons sugar; coat 8 individual custard cups or 2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Place rice mixture in dish; set aside.
Combine bran, flour, walnuts, remaining 1/4 sugar and cinnamon in a bowl. Cut in margarine with pastry blender to consistency of coarse meal.
Sprinkle over rice mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly hot.
Makes 8 servings:
243 calories, 8 g. fat and 0 mg cholesterol.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In Dutch oven over medium heat, melt butter and saute onion until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth, then stir in tomatoes and okra, stirring until mixture thickens slightly.

title: fried mozzarella sticks
directions: Cut cheese into 4 equal parts, then into 6 equal pieces. Place 2 tablespoons milk in bowl and dip each stick in
it, then coat with flour.
Beat egg and remaining teaspoon milk and dip floured cheese sticks in this mixture, then roll in bread crumbs. Freeze 25 minutes.
Fry in hot oil 45 seconds or until golden brown and sticks float to top.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with sauces.

title: broadways cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water and set aside until syrupy. Combine evaporated milk and whipping cream and beat until mixture is quite thick.
In a separate bowl, mix together cream cheese, cottage cheese, lemon juice, vanilla, salt and sugar.
Add cheese mixture to cream mixture.
Add partially set gelatin.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into crust and chill 4 hours.

title: chess squares
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg, butter and water and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: spinach wrap-ups
directions: You will need toothpicks, bowls to hold the vegetables, tablespoon measurement and teaspoon measurement.

title: my pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and molasses.

Add eggs; mix thoroughly. Next add Karo syrup, nuts and flavoring and pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° or 350° (according to the heating of your stove) until a straw or knife blade comes out clean, about one hour.

title: cranberry relish
directions: In blender, grind apples, oranges, cranberries and pineapple. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ground fruit and sugar. Mix well.
Pour into large bowl and chill 6 to 8 hours. Yields 8 to 10 cups.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add 1 cup buttermilk alternately with 3 cups flour.
Add soda to other 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Add to mixture. Dredge fruit and nuts and orange slices in 1 cup flour.
Combine remaining dry ingredients.
Add dates and nuts; blend.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and puddings together.
Add 3 cups juice from strawberries.
If not enough juice, add water to make 3 cups. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Take off stove and cool completely.
Stir in strawberries and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mash butter. Mix with remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips and flour. Mix all together with chocolate chips and flour. Cook at 300° until done.

title: aunt eva's ofield cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add pecans and coconut; mix well.
Pinch off pieces the size of a marble.
Put on cookie sheet and press with finger. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese together, then add pudding.
Mix all together.
Bake cake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When cake is cooled, spread pudding mixture on top, then spread pineapple on top.
Makes a very large cake.

title: artichoke "mock crab"
directions: Wash and drain artichokes.
Mash thoroughly.
Blend with mayonnaise, cheese and seasonings.
Bake in 1-quart casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, orange and apple.
Add sugar and let sit a couple of hours.
Mix jello with 3 cups of boiling water; let cool and stir in cranberry mixture.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onions and celery.
In saucepan, mix soup, milk, evaporated milk, paprika, salt and pepper, mushrooms and chicken. Heat thoroughly.
Add onions and celery to mixture.
Pour over cooked spaghetti covering bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple-orange ice
directions: In
a small saucepan combine water and sugar.
Bring to boil; reduce
heat
and simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly. Stir
in
pineapple
juice
and orange juice.
Pour into
pan. Cover
with foil and freeze until firm.
To serve, break
up mixture until mushy.
Spoon into sherbet glasses and serve.

title: herbed lemon chicken
directions: Marinade:
Mix juice, oil, honey, rosemary, salt and pepper.

title: chocolate pie(makes 1 pie)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Cook on top of stove until mixture becomes creamy.
Pour in cooked pie shell.
Save egg whites from eggs for icing to go on top of pie!

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs, melted butter, coconut and vanilla.
Add milk and mix well.

title: homemade peach ice cream
directions: Combine eggs and sugar in bowl; mix well.
Stir in evaporated milk, half and half, peaches, vanilla and salt.
Pour into 1 gallon ice cream freezer container.
Add milk to fill line. Freeze using manufacturer's instructions.
May substitute favorite fruit for peaches.
Yield:
32 servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat.
Add vanilla, salt, chocolate syrup and Eagle Brand milk; beat until mixed.
Add peanut butter; mix.
Add regular milk until enough for ice cream canister.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put
brown sugar, syrup and margarine in pan; heat, but do not cook.
Beat eggs; add pecans, vanilla and vinegar.
Add all together.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes
or
until
pie
filling
is done.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: sticky bun coffee cake
directions: Place rolls in Bundt pan.
Pour melted oleo over.
Mix all other ingredients together in a separate bowl and sprinkle over rolls.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake in greased pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
Try using a heated 10-inch iron skillet.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cover oatmeal with boiling water.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Cream shortening and add the sugars, eggs and salt.
Add oatmeal mixture, then add the rest of ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost while hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into cubes, line bottom of large casserole, then cover with soups.
Stir together and pour over this the peas, sour cream and stuffing mix.
Sprinkle with 1/4 c. broth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix biscuit mix and sugar until all lumps are gone from sugar. Add eggs, oil and pecans.
Spread in buttered 9 x 14-inch pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
When done, cut in squares.

title: singapore spicy noodles
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the water, ketchup, sugar, cilantro, cornstarch and seasonings.

title: pork chop saute
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
In nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add pork chops; cook until lightly browned, about 5 minutes per side.
Remove chops; cover to keep warm.

title: chicken pate a la maison
directions: Mix ground ham and finely ground chicken breast in bowl and refrigerate up to 1/2 hour.
Add unwhipped whipping cream and mustard; mix well.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Beat egg whites and carefully fold into mixture.

title: fresno fritters
directions: Blend egg and milk; add pancake mix and raisins.
Stir just until mixed.
Fold in corn; do not overbeat.
Drop by teaspoon into hot cooking oil.
Cook until golden brown, about 4 minutes. Serve as a vegetable or with syrup, if desired.

title: seaside dip
directions: Soften cheese in
microwave;
add other ingredients and heat until warm, stirring often.
Serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter and milk one minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix together and drop on board or table to harden.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Spray casserole with Pam.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs the last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cool whip and coconut. Blend. Fold in Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in salad oil until soft.
Beat eggs with seasonings and combine with squash.
Grease a 10-inch square casserole.
Add squash and tomatoes to casserole, then grated cheese; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until set and top is golden.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. bake at 375° for 60 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Put in oven for 4 hours at 325°.

title: crunchy fudge bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt butterscotch chips with peanut butter over low heat until melted. Remove. Add Rice Krispies until well coated. Press 1/2 of mixture into pan. Chill in refrigerator while preparing fudge. Set rest aside.

title: diner meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, pork, oatmeal and eggs.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Pack in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, shaping into a rounded top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Drain off any excess juice.
Serves 8.

title: chicken fried steak with gravy
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper; coat with flour.
Dip floured steak in egg mixture, then in flour again.
In large skillet, brown meat in oil; remove from skillet.
Stir in 2 tablespoons flour and stir until the flour browns.
Stir in water and cook until thickens, stir in milk.
Add meat and simmer for a short time.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and scrub potatoes; pat dry.
Prick a few times with a fork.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until soft.
Cut a thin slice off the top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out the pulp and put in a bowl.

title: strawberry-macadamia nut muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups.
Beat milk, margarine and egg in large bowl.
Stir in flour, sugar, baking powder and salt just until flour is moistened.
Fold in strawberries and nuts.
Divide batter evenly among muffin cups. Sprinkle with sugar if desired.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter; sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheeses.
Put back into oven for 10 more minutes until lightly browned.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain. In large skillet, brown hamburger. Saute onions in butter until soft and yellow. Add tomatoes and simmer gently about 5 minutes.
Add macaroni and salt; mix well. Continue simmering about 10 minutes longer. Wash and remove seeds and membranes from peppers.

Boil 6 minutes in hot water with 1 teaspoon salt. Drain and arrange in buttered casserole. Fill casserole with macaroni and tomato mixture; sprinkle cheese on top. Bake in moderately hot oven (400°) 15 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: earthquake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut.
Place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spread over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until done.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Blend ground chuck, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into balls, roll in flour and brown in skillet.	Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice in
saucepan.
Bring	to
a boil. Add browned meat balls; simmer for 1 hour, without stirring.

title: delicious apple crisp
directions: Divide apples evenly into two lightly greased 6 ounce ovenproof dessert cups.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon flour over each cup.

title: tater topped fish
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Place veggies in large microwave safe cooker, microwave on to package directions. Drain and pat dry with paper towel. Place veggies in bottom of baking pan, top with fish, in large bowl, combine soup, 1 c. of the cheese, milk, black pepper and mix well. Spoon over fish and spread. Top with taters and bake for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with rest of cheese. Bake for another 5 minutes until cheese is melted. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix together and add the eggs, one at a time.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: In the unbaked pie shell, place the apples.
Pour the water and cinnamon over the apples.
Mix together the sugar, flour and margarine until crumbly.
Spread over apples and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve hot with whipped cream.

title: thea's favorite cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased muffin pans or 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° until golden.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients carefully.

title: fruit dip #1
directions: In a medium bowl, blend cream cheese, sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice. Cover and chill in the refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: christmas butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls and press flat with glass. Press with tines of fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: three day slaw
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar, oil, salt to taste, celery seed and mustard.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Let stay in refrigerator overnight.

title: deluxe hash brown potatoes
directions: Put potatoes, soups, sour cream and pepper in large bowl.
Let stand until you can mix ingredients.
Put in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for two hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine everything together except flour and salt.
Beat with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth and creamy. Mix flour and salt together in small bowl.
Add flour mixture to peanut butter mixture, mixing continually.
Drop by 1-1/2 tsp. onto greased baking sheets. Flatten in a crisscross pattern with a fork dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake cookies until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on baking sheets for two minutes.
Transfer to wire racks to cool completely.

title: french market soup
directions: Wash beans; place in large pot.
Add water to cover 2 inches above beans.
Soak overnight.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts water and remaining ingredients, breaking tomatoes up with a fork.
Bring to a boil; reduce the heat.
Cover; simmer 2 to 4 hours, depending on how "mushy" you like beans.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all ingredients except noodles. Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes. Bake another 30 to 45 minutes, uncovered. Stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles.

title: wonder soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts tender; remove.
Add bouillon cubes and set aside.
Saute onion, carrots and celery.
Add vegetables to broth (including the bouillon).
Boil gently for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add instant potatoes to thicken soup.
May need to add more water.
Chop chicken and add.
May use a ham bone instead of chicken.
Use same veggies and cubes of ham, but omit the chicken bouillon.

title: mexicana antipasto
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and garlic salt.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine avocado, lemon juice, tomato and green chilies.
Use this as the second layer.
Sprinkle on the bacon, green onion and olives.
Spread taco sauce over all.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serve cold with corn chips, taco chips or crackers.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt the Hershey bar with low heat.
Add Cool Whip and mix. Pour into the pie crust.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon bits until brown.
Put with cooked, sliced potatoes. Add onion, salt and pepper. Set aside.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs. Pour batter in a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese, butter and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk, then egg and vanilla until smooth.
Pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake 55 minutes or until done (when wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean).
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: peach dessert
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add peaches and juice.
Add dry cake mix, coconut and nuts.
Drizzle melted oleo over top.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Combine cornstarch, soup mix and water together; let set. Heat oil on high; stir-fry vegetables and spices until crisp.
Add soup mixture and heat, stirring.
Serve with hot, plain rice.

title: goulash
directions: In a large skillet, saut onions and bell peppers with 1 teaspoon of oil. In a large pot, boil noodles until tender. Add hamburger to onions and bell pepper and brown. When done, drain hamburger and noodles. Combine in large pot. Add tomato juice and bring to a boil. Ready to serve.

title: julekake(christmas bread)
directions: Dissolve
yeast in water.
Mix milk and butter in bowl. When lukewarm,
add
egg,
yeast,
sugar,
salt, cardamon and fruit. Add 2
cups flour and mix well.
Gradually add remaining flour, saving
some
for kneading.
Knead on floured board until smooth. Place
in greased bowl.
Cover;
let rise until double in bulk. Punch
down
and divide in half.
Form into 2 round loaves and place
on greased pan. Cover; let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar while warm.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt into margarine mixture; mix until well blended.
Stir in bananas and walnuts.
Spoon into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until loaf tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: spinach balls(microwave)
directions: Microwave spinach in covered casserole on High 4 to 5 minutes, or until defrosted.
Drain, pressing out excess liquid. Mix with remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls, about 1 1/2 teaspoons each.
Place on wax paper lined baking sheet. Cover and freeze overnight.
Pack in freezer container.
Label.
Freeze no longer than 2 weeks.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Dip chicken in egg, then into bread crumbs. Brown chicken in oil on both sides. Pour tomato sauce into an 8 x 8 pan. Lay chicken on top of sauce. Top with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 25 minutes.

title: sirloin tips over rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet. Cook onion until tender. Salt and pepper meat and dredge in flour. Brown meat on all sides. Add water and onion soup mix. Reduce heat and cook until meat is tender, about 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: graham cracker delights
directions: Melt margarine; mix with sugar.
Boil 3 minutes; add nuts. Spoon over crackers.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix
together thoroughly. If salad seems dry, add tablespoon of chicken broth.

title: zucchini lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spread 1/2 cup sauce over the bottom of dish.
Arrange uncooked lasagne noodles in dish, breaking off to make fit.
Combine Ricotta, eggs, basil, oregano and Parmesan cheese; spread over noodles. Top with more noodles and 1/2 cup more sauce.
Combine zucchini, salt, pepper and flour.
Spoon into baking dish and spread to make a level layer.
Top with more noodles and sauce.
Combine zucchini, salt, pepper and flour.
Spoon into baking dish and spread to make a level layer.
Top with more noodles and sauce. Cover dish with foil, place on a rimmed baking sheet and bake 60 or so minutes.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake about 15 to 20 minutes, until cheese is brown.
Remove and let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Enjoy!

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients with an electric mixer and pour into the dish.
Then mix 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sugar.
Sprinkle on top of pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm.
(This tends to bubble over so put in a large enough dish that will allow for this.)

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Mix all ingredients, except parsley.
Spoon into lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with Melba rounds.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 3 cups.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into bite-size flowerets.
Cut and stem broccoli using tops only.
Add onion then mix rest of ingredients. Pour over vegetables and toss lightly.
Refrigerate and let stand 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: cowboy supper
directions: Brown ground round. Rinse in colander and add to baking pan. Add remaining ingredients. Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crazy peach pie
directions: Put margarine in loaf pan and melt.
Sift together sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk to flour mixture.
Pour over the melted margarine in the pan.
Then pour peaches over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Pour milk over 1 cup bread crumbs.
Combine squash, onion, 1 tablespoon butter, eggs, salt and pepper; blend well.
Add to bread mix; stir and blend.
Spoon into lightly greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine remaining bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice(low sugar, salt and fat)
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute rice in hot oil until lightly browned.
Add the onion, garlic and salt.
Cook over low heat until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes; cook over medium heat until softened.
Add water; cover and simmer until water is absorbed.
Stir in broth, peas and carrots; cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, about 10 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain excess fat.
Add onion soup mix and water; stir.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a large casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain lima beans and kidney beans. Fry bacon; add onion and simmer. Drain grease. Add pork and beans and butter beans. Mix all beans together. Bring brown sugar, catsup and vinegar to boil. Pour over bean mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease baking pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into medium-size bowl.
Cut in butter and shortening.
Stir in enough milk to make soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly.
Pat out 1/2-inch thick. Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: citrus punch
directions: In two large pitchers or a large punch bowl, combine the first five ingredients.
Gently stir in soda.
Serve immediately. Yield: 4 quarts.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken;
debone and
remove
skin.
To broth, add cream of chicken soup, butter and salt and pepper to taste.

title: christmas rock cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and brown sugar.
Add the eggs; mix well.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 13 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.
These will keep in the freezer for quite a while.
Makes 400.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix together crunched up vanilla wafers, melted butter, sugar, milk and eggs together.
Mix well.
Then add flaked coconut and chopped nuts.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: barbecued beef sandwiches
directions: Place all ingredients in skillet and break up with fork.
Cook until thick, about 30 minutes.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns. Makes 10 to 12.
Excellent for a picnic.
Pack in a wide mouth thermos.

title: no-cook barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar and shake well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Use on pork or chicken, also good on baked ham or ribs.

title: crockpot easy swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into 5 or 6 serving pieces.
Place in crockpot. Add dry onion mix, water, and soup.
Cover and cook 6 to 8 hours. Excellent with mashed potatoes.
If you like lots of gravy use 2 packages soup mix and 2 cans of soup.

title: eggless, butterless, milkless snack cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and boil 3 minutes.
Cool and add water and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dad's tuna salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.

title: sunshine shake
directions: In a blender, combine orange juice, milk, water, vanilla and ice cubes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Place blueberries on bottom of a 10 x 6-inch greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon
juice.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and cinnamon; add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove to wire cooling rack.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: seafood dip
directions: Chop seafood. Cream remaining ingredients. Combine everything and mix well. Chill at least 2 hours. Serve with assorted crackers, chips or veggies.

title: halibut casserole
directions: Boil halibut about 15 minutes in water (until it nearly flakes).
Do not overcook fish.
Drain fish.
Leave fish in fair size chunks, about 1 1/2 inches.
Put soup in a greased casserole dish.
Add 1 soup can of milk.
Add fish.
Top with egg, then cheese, then bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve on biscuits or toast points.
Serves 6.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash, onions, bell pepper and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, rinse in cold water 2 times.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes.
Seal in jars.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: korean beef patties
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into four balls and flatten into patties.
Broil, grill or pan-fry until done.

title: grilled vegetable salad
directions: Stir together first 7 ingredients in a large bowl. Set aside. Cut carrots and next 5 ingredients into large pieces. Add to vinegar mixture. Let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Drain veggies, reserving vinegar mixture. Arrange veggies evenly in a grill basket. Grill covered with grill lid, over medium high heat (350 - 400) 15 to 20 minutes or until crisp-tender, turning occasionally. Toss veggies in reserved vinegar mixture. Serve immediately or cover and chill up to 8 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken for a king
directions: Blend onion soup and sour cream.
Let stand for 2 hours.
In large roasting pan, place chicken, sherry, water and sprinkle with seasonings.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Chickens may be cooked the day before.
Remove from roaster, cover loosely and allow to cool.
Combine 2 cups hot broth with the cream of mushroom soup and slowly stir in the sour cream mixture to prevent curdling.
Cook rice according to directions on box. Skin and bone chicken and cut up the meat.
Combine with cooked rice.
Pour sauce over all.
Heat uncovered for 30 to 45 minutes at 250°.
Sprinkle canned onions over top and serve (I return to oven for about 5 minutes to brown).
This recipe freezes well.

title: bacon-stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and dry. Rub with a little butter or oil and bake directly on oven rack at 400° for about 1 hour or until fork-tender. Cut a long oval slice from one side of potato
and scoop out into a bowl. Add butter, sour cream, egg, salt and pepper. Beat well. Stir in crisp, crumbled bacon.
Pile back into 6 potato shells, mounding the potatoes high (that's why you baked two extra potatoes).
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until heated through. Serves 6.

title: stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, combine
beef or chicken with soy sauce and ginger.
Let stand 15 to 30 minutes.
Preheat 1 tablespoon of oil in a pan or wok, uncovered, at medium-high for about 2 minutes. Add about half of vegetables and stir for 2 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove vegetables and heat 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add half of your meat.
Stir 2 to 3 minutes.
Repeat with other half of meat.
Combine water, cornstarch and sugar.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Reduce heat to low for serving.
Serve with rice.

title: pecan jumbo fudge pie
directions: Cream butter; gradually add brown sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until blended. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in melted chocolate, vanilla, pecans and whipped cream.

Pour mixture into Oreo crust. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Cool completely on a wire rack. Before serving, pipe sweetened cream around edge of entire pie or on each piece and drizzle with chocolate syrup. Garnish, if desired. Yield: One 9-inch pie.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Drain and discard pickle juice. Slice or chunk pickles and return to jar. Boil sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved. Pour over pickles and refrigerate. Best if let set a couple of weeks.

title: easy southern chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with butter or margarine.
Evenly layer chicken in the bottom of the greased pan.
Spread frozen vegetables on top of chicken. Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Mix together cans of soups; evenly spread soup mixture over vegetables.
In a bowl at medium speed, mix Bisquick, milk and shortening until smooth.
Pour mixture over top of vegetables. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 5 minutes before serving. Yields 6 servings.

title: easy peach-cheese pie
directions: Blend together flour and brown sugar.
Cut margarine and orange rind into flour mixture.
Stir in enough cold water to form mixture into a ball.
Pat dough into a 9-inch glass pie plate. Microwave at Medium 3 to 4 minutes.
Crust will puff up and will settle down.
Cool before filling.

title: heart smart beef casserole(microwave)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brush 2 pita breads with Kraft House Italian dressing.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Top each pita with 2 single cheese slices and pizza toppings: chopped peppers, mushrooms, chopped ham and onion.
Drizzle with dressing.
Bake for 1 to 2 minutes.
Cut and serve.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Heat
oven
Cut ham and cheese slices in half lengthwise.
Place
ham on flat surface.
Place cheese on top. Divide
asparagus evenly in 8 parts.
Place at end of each ham and cheese
slice
and roll up securely (jelly roll fashion). Place, seam
side
down,
in
8-inch square baking dish.
Set aside.

title: imperial shrimp (peking)
directions: Mix thoroughly dried shrimp with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
In hot deep oil (375° to 400°), fry the shrimp until no longer opaque.
Drain.
In 2 tablespoons oil, stir-fry 1 tablespoon minced ginger, 1 tablespoon minced scallion, 1/2 minced sweet red pepper and 1/2 minced onion just until onion is transparent.
Add 4 tablespoons catsup, 1 tablespoon sugar and 4 tablespoons chicken stock.
Add hot chili or pepper oil (1/2 teaspoon or more, to taste).
Turn heat to high and pour shrimp into the sauce mixture.
As soon as piping hot, serve.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Spread batter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan that has been greased and floured and bake as instructed.
Boil crushed pineapple with juice and sugar for 3 minutes.
While cake is still warm, punch holes in top and slowly pour pineapple mixture over cake a little at a time to let soak in.
Continue until all syrup is used.
Allow cake to cool completely before icing.
Cream butter and cream cheese; add powdered sugar and beat until creamy.
Add nuts and continue beating until spreading consistency.
Spread over top of cake. Cut in squares and serve directly from pan.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: slovenian or polish sausage & sauerkraut
directions: Boil sausage on medium heat for 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Melt butter in skillet.
Chop onions and add to skillet, cook until transparent.
Drain sauerkraut and add to skillet mixing and turning until light brown.
Cut sausages into 1/4 inch (bite size) pieces and add to sauerkraut mixture.
Cook 5 - 10 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: oven-fried fish
directions: Cut fish into serving-size steaks or fillets.
Dip in milk combined with salt, then in bread crumbs.
Place in a single layer in a greased shallow pan.
Pour on melted butter or oil.
Bake at 400 degrees about 20 minutes until fish flakes easily with fork. Serve with lemon wedge or Tartar Sauce.

title: egg custard
directions: Heat milk, sugar and butter in saucepan.
Add salt.
Heat until butter melts.
Beat eggs; add hot mixture to eggs and add vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: baked lima bean casserole
directions: Use 3 cans of beans with juice; reserve juice from 1 can in case of drying out.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with gingersnaps. Cover with beans.
Mix brown sugar and catsup together; pour over beans.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover and top casserole with bacon.
Return to oven with no cover and bake another 20 minutes longer.
Yum yum.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except marshmallows, together well.
Pour into a well-greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. When casserole is done, remove from oven and top with marshmallows.
Put it back into oven and bake until marshmallows are a golden brown.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Take hamburger and pat it in a roaster or casserole dish. Drain can of green beans and put over the hamburger.
Then put Tater Tots on top and add the can of cream of celery soup.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugar-free cream pie
directions: Mix together peanut butter, honey and Rice Krispies.
Slice one banana and put on top.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla; pour in crust.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: hot fudge sauce ii
directions: Combine ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Stir over low heat until chocolate melts.
Makes 1 cup.

title: sourdough chocolate cake
directions: Mix sourdough starter, milk and flour.
Let stand 2 or 3 hours in a warm place until bubbly and there is a clean sour milk odor.

title: carolyn's fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme until smooth.
Add orange rind and ginger.
Chill before serving.

title: frozen slush punch
directions: Mix water and sugar. Boil for 5 minutes and cool. Mash bananas. Add remaining ingredients. Freeze in three 1/2-gallon cartons. Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving and cut through with knife to break up. Place one carton in punch bowl and pour 2 (16 ounce) bottles of 7-Up over it.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello; stir until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries; stir until thawed.
Add crushed pineapple and mashed bananas.
Pour half into an 8-inch square dish.
Chill until set. Spread sour cream over all and chill a little, then spread rest of jello and fruit mixture over sour cream.
Chill well before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add spaghetti and sauce.
Layer noodles, hamburger, sauce and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cut tortillas in fourths.
Mix soup, milk, chilies and onions. Butter or Pam a casserole pan.
Line bottom of pan with tortillas.
Next, add a layer of chicken, then 1/2 of soup mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with soup mixture.
Top with cheese.
You can make 24 hours ahead of time and refrigerate. This allows flavor to mix through.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 1 hour.
(You may not need the full package of tortillas.)

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine vegetables and salt in a glass or enamel container and let stand overnight.

title: okra, bacon, rice delight
directions: Have rice precooked already.
Cut bacon up into 1-inch pieces. Fry until done.
Take drippings up along with bacon.
Cut okra up; salt, pepper, flour and fry.
Mix bacon, okra and drippings together.
Combine rice, stirring together.
Put on low heat 5 minutes or until ready to serve.

title: refreshing fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Set aside.
Combine sugar and egg in a saucepan.
Gradually stir in reserved pineapple juice and lemon juice. Add margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cool dressing.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish. Add rice over melted margarine.
Pour chicken soup and 1 can of water plus onion soup and 1/2 can of water over long grain rice.
Salt and pepper chicken breasts to taste.
Place over rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops from green peppers; discard seeds and membranes. Chop tops to make 1/2 cup.
Cook green pepper cups, uncovered, in boiling water for 5 minutes; invert to drain.
Sprinkle insides of peppers lightly with 1/8 teaspoon salt.
In skillet, cook the beef, onion and chopped green pepper tops until meat is brown and onion is tender; drain off fat.
Stir in the chopped tomato, croutons, half of the shredded cheese, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and the garlic salt.
Spoon mixture into peppers.
Place peppers in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake about 5 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Cook carrots, celery and onions in oleo in 4-quart heavy pan for 10 minutes or until transparent.
Stir in Bisquick mix, paprika and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chicken broth. Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly 1 minute. Reduce heat; stir in half and half, cheese and beer.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve topped with popped corn, if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Delicious.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Divide into 2 greased loaf pans.
Line pans with wax paper. Pour mixture evenly into each pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: wild sex on the beach
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix well.
Add enough food coloring to make the desired color.

title: country cobbler
directions: Mix and let stand the fruit and sugar.
Cream butter, sugar and add remaining ingredients.
Butter a casserole or oblong baking dish and spread batter in bottom of dish.
Pour fruit and sugar mixture on top.
Cover with 1 cup boiling water and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipping cream.

title: supper a la king
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook green pepper and onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup and milk; blend well.
Stir in meat, cheese and pimento. Cook 5 minutes more or until heated thoroughly.
Serve over rice. Makes about 3 1/2 cups sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: low-fat applesauce muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat muffin tins with nonstick spray. Combine muffin mix and raisins in medium mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until just blended.
Fill prepared muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: white sangria
directions: Boil sugar and water until clear.
Cool.
Take 3 slices from center of each fruit and save for garnish.
Squeeze remaining fruit and pour white wine and sugar syrup over fruit and juice. Let it steep for several hours or overnight.
Remove fruit.
Add soda when ready to serve.
Pour over lots of ice and garnish with slices.
Makes 24 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in buttered baking dish; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma elliott's chili sauce
directions: Mix tomatoes, onions, peppers, vinegar and salt in large kettle.
Add spices and brown sugar.
Cook down until thick.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 16 pints.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour and oatmeal.
Run through blender until powdery.
Add salt, baking soda and powder.
Mix all ingredients together and add chips and Hershey bar.
Place golf ball sized cookies 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 6 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: ground beef and rice
directions: Brown beef.
Add rice and soup mix, then fill skillet with water.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries thoroughly.
Put into 1 quart pot with water; bring to a boil.
Add sugar, gelatin and walnuts.
Stir well. Pour into jello ring and chill.

title: pan rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast into water; let stand a few minutes, then stir until dissolved.
Pour hot milk over butter, sugar and salt.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast, eggs and half of the flour; beat well. Add more flour to make a dough that will not stick to bowl.
Put into greased bowl; cover and let rise until doubled (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down and turn out on board.
Shape in 50 balls and put close together in pan.
Let double 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese canapes
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger in a little oil.
Add dry ingredients and cheese; stir until melted.
Put on party rye; bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
These are great for entertaining.

title: my great grandmother's beet jam
directions: Wash and peel beets.
Put through meat grinder or grate them. (I use my food processor.)
Barely cover with water and cook slowly until tender.
Add sugar, ginger and lemon juice and rind. Cook until thick and clear, at least 1 hour.
Add chopped nuts. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Cook tomatoes, butter and brown sugar until boiling.
Add cornstarch.
Continue cooking until thick.
In glass baking dish, add tomato pudding and bread cubes in layers, commencing with bread and finishing with tomato mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: jessica's favorite cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross on each cookie with a fork dipped in water.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden.
Cool off cookie sheet for 1 minute, then remove cookies.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and cocoa together; boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend all ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Cookies will harden and no baking is necessary.
May add 1/2 cup chopped pecans, if desired.

title: tomato pie
directions: Butter an 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Pat canned biscuits out to form a crust.
Slice tomatoes to cover biscuits.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Spread over tomatoes.
Mix cheese and mayonnaise (add more mayonnaise if mixture is too thick to spread over pie).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Allow to cool and set for about 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: With a mixer, blend sugar and eggs until creamy and fluffy. Add peanut butter.
Drop in 1 1/4-inch balls onto greased cookie sheet about 2 inched apart.

title: favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour mixture.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas and then dump everything into a large bowl and mix well.
Great served with vanilla wafers.

title: lemon buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple with Jell-O and heat until completely dissolved. Cool completely.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: tandy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Hershey bar.
Will be runny.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While hot spread smooth peanut butter on cake.
Let it cool.
Melt and spread Hershey bar over peanut butter.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix altogether; put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cherry winks
directions: Crush cornflakes and set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine butter and sugar and beat until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients with nuts, dates and cherries; mix well.

title: red cake
directions: Mix cocoa, red color, water and vanilla.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and cocoa mix. Blend.
Next add alternately the buttermilk and flour.
Last, mix soda and vinegar. Fold into batter lightly.
Bake in two 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pasta with tuna sauce
directions: In small saucepan, cook chopped onion with small amount of olive oil until transparent.
Empty can of tuna into pan, stirring to blend.
Add parsley, dash of salt and pepper to taste and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook linguini or penne.
Drain (reserve some of water to add to tuna sauce, if needed.)
Pour sauce over pasta and serve.
No cheese, please.

title: egg pie crust
directions: Put egg in a measuring cup; add enough water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Mix flour and shortening until as fine as cornmeal; then add salt.
Add the egg liquid.
Mix well with a fork until it forms a soft ball.
Sprinkle flour on board.
Knead dough.
Cut in half. Makes 2 crusts.
Roll out to make crust.
Bake unfilled crust at 350° until brown.

title: cheese sauce for vegetables
directions: Heat
margarine
over
low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly,
until	mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir
in
milk.
Heat
to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil
and
stir
1	minute.
Stir
in cheese and pepper sauce. Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Good over cauliflower and broccoli.

title: sour cream-cottage cheese garden salad
directions: Blend sour cream with cottage cheese.
Stir in chilled vegetables, salt and pepper.
Serve in lettuce-lined bowl; strip with green pepper rings or spoon into tomato cups.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt evaporated milk and caramels in double boiler; set aside. Mix cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and chopped walnuts.
Press 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle chocolate chips over this and then the caramel mixture over this.
Crumble (if too moist, just press and put on top) rest of dough over caramel mixture.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: banana dip
directions: Mix bananas, brown sugar and honey in blender until smooth. Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate.
Serve with strawberries.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and cook for 5 minutes.

title: easy peach crumble
directions: Place peaches in a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate.
Combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add butter and cut into mixture until resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle mixture over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
183 calories.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine and cool.
Add all other ingredients and mix. Serve cold.

title: hot dog and noodles
directions: Bring tomato juice to a boil.
Stir in soup mix and noodles. Reduce heat to simmer for 15 minutes.
Add hot dogs (halved and cut crosswise).
Cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Just before serving, add cheese.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix all ingredients; boil 5 minutes.
Seal with wax.
These preserves taste just like strawberries!

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar and add all ingredients. Chill.

title: tomato soup(to can)
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients and strain.
Mix salt, sugar, flour and butter; add to above hot mixture.
Cook until flour is cooked.
Put into pint jars; process 10 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.
To serve, add equal amount of milk and heat.

title: apricot snack loaf
directions: Soak apricots in hot water 15 minutes; drain.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Add nuts and apricots; set aside.
Mix margarine and sugar, then stir in egg, corn syrup and orange juice.
Stir in flour mixture, mixing well.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; cook on low heat or double boiler until mixture thickens.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Top with meringue, brown in oven.
Cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape in ball.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables as directed; drain.
Mix half of the crackers with melted margarine; spread in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix vegetables, cheese, onion, celery and mayonnaise in bowl.
Pour remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to the directions on the box.
Put half of cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Cool for 10 minutes.
Unwrap caramels and melt with butter and Eagle Brand milk, then cool.
Pour this over baked layers.
This will be stiff so do not pour in one spot.
Add last half of mix. Top with chocolate chips and chopped pecans.
Return to oven and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and serve in pan.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popped corn in a roasting pan.
In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, oleo or butter, corn syrup and salt.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Take from heat and add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring occasionally.

title: oven simmered beef stew
directions: Place beef cubes in 3-quart casserole with tight lid.
In a small bowl combine onion soup, mushroom gravy, pepper, wine and water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and add carrots, potatoes and mushrooms.
Return to oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Add chopped parsley, if desired.

title: slush punch
directions: Boil 2 cups boiling water and sugar for 3 minutes and set aside. Let cool. Mix Jell-O and water well until dissolved. Set aside and let cool. Mix pineapple juice, lemonade and 3 cans cold water well. After everything is cooled, mix all ingredients together and freeze. Let stand out 2 to 3 hours before using and then mix with Sprite.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Beat egg and set aside.
Combine broth and corn; bring to a boil.
While boiling, lower heat and stir in beaten egg.
Serves 3.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl.
Let stand at least 1 hour before serving.

title: pineapple and grapefruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and sugar. Cut in grapefruit and pour in juice.
Add pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cut up chicken (if using a whole chicken).
Boil until done. Skin chicken.
Combine soups, broth, tomatoes and jalapeno peppers (diced) together.
Warm until smooth and remove from stove.
After sauce is ready, layer Doritos, chicken, onions, sauce and cheese. Cook in oven for about 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Use your judgment on cooking time.
You don't want it to be soupy or dry. Oven temperature should be around 325°.

title: chilled potatoes in creamy herb sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring small amount of water to boil. Add potatoes; cook, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until tender. Drain and cool.
Slice and place in a bowl.
Toss with peas and bell pepper.
Add yogurt, parsley, green onions, basil, salt and pepper. Toss gently to coat.
Cover; chill until ready to serve. Yields 8 servings.

title: banana fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bananas.
Peel and slice bananas in half lengthwise and again vertically.
Dip bananas in batter and place them in a frying pan or grill which is lightly greased with shortening.
Fry until lightly brown on both sides. Remove from pan and sprinkle with confectioners powdered sugar. Serve warm.

title: peach enchiladas
directions: Boil water, sugar and margarine for about 10 minutes.
Mix together pineapple and peaches.
Roll fruit in flour tortillas and arrange in pan.
Pour hot mixture over and bake about 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn enchiladas to brown bottom side.
Remove when brown.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix above ingredients and stuff into uncooked manicotti shells (one 8 ounce package).

title: grandma's sunshine cake
directions: Separate the whites and yolks of 5 eggs.
Add water to the yolks and beat.
Add sugar slowly into the yolks and beat well. Add boiling water to the egg yolk mixture and beat well.
Then add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Then fold into the yolk mixture.
Pour cake mixture into an angel food cake pan (separates into two parts).
Put into a cold oven set at 300°. Bake 1 hour.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Blend all dry ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Add the egg, oil and milk.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into well-greased pan (Crisco).
Use 8-inch square or 11 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot. Serves 6.

title: jam cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and beat.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; combine with first mixture and mix well.
Form 1-inch balls on greased baking sheet.
Flatten with teaspoon, making small indentations in center of each cookie. Fill with preserves.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in moderate 325° to 350° oven.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine zucchini, onion, Stove Top (crumbs only), butter, carrots and celery.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl, mix soup, sour cream and Stove Top seasonings.
Grease well the casserole dish. Start layering from the two bowls, starting with the soup mix.
Judge the amount of each layer so that your
last layer is a soup layer.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, powdered sugar and milk for 2 minutes on low speed.
Fold in Cool Whip into pudding mixture; set aside.
Lightly grease (with Pam) bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line bottom of pan with a layer of whole graham crackers (break in half to make fit, if needed).
Pour half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers.
Pour remainder of pudding over that.
Put another layer of graham crackers on top, then frost with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate; cut into squares to serve.

title: lobster bisque
directions: In a pot simmer the lobster meat and butter for 5 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients and stir.
Let it cook until serving temperature.
The longer you let it sit the more flavor.

title: beef exceptional
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add mushrooms and onions.
Cook until tender.
Set aside.
In another frying pan, cook ground beef, adding salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Drain ground beef and add to onions and mushrooms.
Add sour cream to taste, mixing well.
Serve over warm egg noodles.

title: old fashioned vegetable soup(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: In large saucepan, combine beef shank, salt, thyme, peppercorns, bay leaf, allspice, bouillon and water.
Simmer, covered, 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove beef shank, peppercorns and bay leaf.
Cut meat from bone and return to soup.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and continue simmering about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: refrigerator cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage; add salt and let set at room temperature for 1 hour.
Squeeze out liquid.
Add shredded carrot and green pepper. Combine vinegar, sugar, water and spices.
Boil 2 minutes.
Cool and pour over cabbage.
Will keep up to 3 weeks in fridge.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with your hands until crumbly, then take out 1 cup of mixture. To remaining mixture, add butter and egg. Stir well. Mixture will be slightly lumpy. Pour in greased pan. Sprinkle crumbs over top, then sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: bonnie's baked ham
directions: Place ham in large piece of foil.
Pour Pepsi over ham and seal with foil.
Bake overnight at 200°.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Combine tomatoes, 1 tablespoon olive oil and tomato paste in medium saucepan.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: pea casserole
directions: Stir soup into peas, mixing well and pour into casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Dot with butter or melt and pour over top.
Bake at 400° until top is brown and cheese is melted.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan. Cook 25 minutes at 350° in oven.

title: barbecued (venison) deer
directions: Simmer margarine and onions until light brown.
Pour in catsup, water, mustard, lemon juice and vinegar.
Stir until well blended; pour over sliced deer in baking dish.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300° or simmer in electric frypan for 2 hours at 250°.

title: chili dip
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl.
Place can in microwave 2 minutes at Medium power.
Place can of chili mix in bowl, add green chilies and mix.
Add cheese; mix well.
Place back in microwave; heat 3 minutes on Medium power.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: blueberry crumb cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in butter to make crumbs; set aside.
Combine cake mix, pudding, sour cream, oil and eggs.
Blend at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle berries evenly over batter, then sprinkle crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "lite" banana split dessert(140 calories per serving)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix crushed cereal, margarine and Sweet 'N Low in bowl.
Pat mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: gourmet potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, uncovered, in boiling salted water for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool 1 hour and slice into bite size pieces.
Grind hazelnuts in blender or food processor.
Combine nuts, salad dressing, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Place potatoes, green beans and artichokes in a large bowl.
Toss gently with dressing. Chill 1 hour or more.

title: joe froggers
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and rum extract; beat well. Add flour mixture and water alternately, beating until well blended after each addition.
Wrap dough in foil; chill overnight.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Top with chopped lettuce and chopped tomato.

title: picnic hot dogs
directions: Combine beer, chili sauce, onions and mustard in saucepan. Add hot dogs.
Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Serve on rolls.
