title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl until well blended.
Spread on a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese with powdered sugar, then add Cool Whip.
Pour over first layer.
Make sure first layer is cool.
Pour glaze over 2nd layer, then add strawberries on top.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: wendy's lasagna
directions: Combine first six ingredients and simmer until thick.

Soften noodles while doing that and then mix the following six ingredients together. Put soft noodles in bottom of pan, put in cheese mixture, then meat, then mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers until you fill the 9x13 pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Let set 10 minutes.

title: barley bean medley
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add barley and continue sauteing until barley is light brown.
Add beans, broth, parsley, bacon, coriander and salt.
Cover.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to a simmer for about 1 hour, adding additional broth or water if necessary or until beans and barley are tender and all moisture is absorbed.
Serves 4.

title: chicken noodle dish
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Put in skillet or wok and brown; set aside.
Cook noodles according to bag; set aside.
Cook broccoli and set aside.
Mix all ingredients together and warm a few minutes.
Add milk to make is saucy.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift sugar and cocoa.
Melt cheese and butter over low heat, stirring often.
Pour melted mixture into sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix.
Turn into light buttered pan.
Keep refrigerated!

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: Combine stuffing, raisins, applesauce and walnuts.
Place stuffing mixture on 2 pieces of turkey.
Roll stuffing with turkey slices.
Put roll-ups
in pan.
Cook soup following directions on can.
Pour soup over roll-ups.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Beat egg white and water in bowl until frothy.
Add walnuts; mix well.
Coat walnuts with mixture of sugar, salt and cinnamon. Spread in single layer on baking sheet, covered with aluminum foil. Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and break apart.

title: raspberry ice cream
directions: Put berries in the blender and process until smooth.
Press puree through a sieve to remove the seeds.
Set the puree aside. Beat the eggs and sugar with an electric mixer until they are thick and have a lemon color.
Now add the puree and the remaining ingredients.
Pour the mixture into the freezer of a 1 gallon freezer.
Follow the directions for your freezer.
Ripen 1 hour. Yields 2 quarts.
This is a great end of July summer treat!

title: chili con queso
directions: Cook onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons of butter until soft. Add tomatoes and simmer until thick.
Add chilies.
Make sauce with remaining butter, flour and cream.
Add cheese, cut into 1-inch cubes (approximately).
Cook until smooth and thick.
Then add to tomato mixture.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Serve warm in chafing dish with chips.

title: low-fat macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°; cook macaroni and drain and rinse and set aside.
Melt margarine in heavy saucepan over moderate heat; add flour and 1/4 cup of milk.
Whisk until well blended.
Add remaining milk and cook about 2 minutes; remove from heat and add all but 2 teaspoons Parmesan cheese.
Stir into macaroni and salt to taste.
Add cottage cheese and spoon into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered about 30 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Lightly brown onion in 4 tablespoons margarine.
Thinly slice squash and add to frying pan.
Cook on low heat until squash is soft.
Add rest of margarine (4 tablespoons).
In a separate bowl, mix cheeses, eggs and salt.
Blend into squash mixture.
Pour into a large, greased casserole.
Bake about one hour in a 350° oven.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually add sugar and vanilla. Beat until stiff (8 to 10 minutes).
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cookies on cookie sheet covered with foil (saves washing cookie sheet). Turn off oven before putting cookies in and leave the cookies in the oven overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook shells and let cool.
Dice all other ingredients and mix with shells.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice sweet potato.
Cook, uncovered, in skillet with butter.
When tender, sprinkle sugar over top while warm.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Fry bacon.
Add onion and celery; saute until translucent. Add the flour, pepper and salt; cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add water, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and parsley.
Cook until sugar is dissolved and mixture is thickened.
Place potatoes in 9 x 13-inch or flat casserole pan.
Pour hot mixture over potatoes; ease through entire dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except bread.
Hollow out a loaf of rye or pumpernickel bread and fill with the dip.
Cut up remaining bread in pieces or serve with crackers.
When dip is gone, the bowl may be eaten.

title: quick cheddar bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix and cheese. Add milk and eggs, mixing just until moistened. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Remove from pan and serve warm. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Combine eggs, oil and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and last the zucchini.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Use a 10 x 15-inch pan or 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.

title: char's artichoke dip
directions: Break up artichokes and mix together with rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with pinah rye chips or Win Schuler's garlic bar-chips.
(May substitute other chips.)
This is so good!!

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs one at a time.
Add flour to batter a little at a time.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: stuffed onions
directions: Very carefully hollow out onion, leaving shell 1/2-inch thick. Place shell in saucepan with water to cover; bring to boil and cook 6 minutes.
Place bacon in skillet set over medium heat until just about transparent.
Add chopped onions; saute 3 minutes until onions begin to color.
Remove and mix with the parsley, bread crumbs and marjoram.
Stir well and add beaten egg, Parmesan and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in tomato pieces.
Spoon stuffing in onion shell.
Place in greased baking dish, cover dish with foil and bake 1 hour at 375° until they are tender when pierced with fork.
Let sit about 5 minutes before serving.

title: dressing for cole slaw
directions: Makes about 1 1/2 gallons.
Use for cabbage and carrots.

title: magic potato chip cookies
directions: Mix condensed milk and peanut butter.
Add the coconut and potato chips.
Drop the mixture by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together, smooth out in an 8 x 8 pan and allow to set.

title: chocolate chip snack squares
directions: In small mixing bowl combine margarine, honey, milk, egg, orange juice concentrate and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Stir into liquid ingredients.
Mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Spread mixture in oiled and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into 15 squares.

title: blender coconut custard pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender for 2 minutes.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: soft, chewy cookies
directions: Beat egg in a large bowl; mix in cake mix.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well, using a fork.
Drop by teaspoon in powdered sugar.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix sugar and water; bring to a boil, add jello and dissolve. Add cherry pie filling and place back on burner; get very hot.
Add pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Stir several times while cooling.
Makes a large salad.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and layer in the bottom of a casserole dish. Saute onion and put on top of squash.
Add cream of chicken soup. Cover with cracker crumbs, then sprinkle with Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine
sugar,
milk, cocoa and butter in large saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute only.
Remove from heat
and stir
in
vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Pour into a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: bertha's orange chicken with rice
directions: In large pan, put chicken, orange juice, onion and seasonings; cover.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add rice; cook for 20 minutes or until rice is done.

title: chicken or pork with rice
directions: Remove all skin and fat from thighs or pork ribs; put into pot and cover with water.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Boil until liquid boils down to about 1-inch in bottom of pot.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: velvet cheese soup
directions: In a soup pot, combine the butter, onions, celery, carrots, and bell pepper.
Saute until vegetables are tender but not browned.
In a large saucepan, heat the broth, half and half, and milk.
Add the flour to the vegetables.
Mix well.
Add the boiling water and the milk mixture.
Stir well. Add the cheese in small pieces.
Reduce heat to low and stir until cheese melts. Taste and adjust seasoning, if needed.
Makes 1/2 gal.

title: squash casserole
directions: Beat egg, add squash, sugar, bread, salt & pepper & 1/2 can of Onion rings.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or microwave for 10 minutes.
Pour remaining onion rings over top of casserole and bake for 5 minutes or microwave for 2 minutes.

title: mince pie with sour cream topping
directions: Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Pour on top of baked cake and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: eggs rebel
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix sausage with bread and distribute evenly in baking pan.
Throw in Cheddar cheese. Mix remaining ingredients in the blender and pour over bread.
Pat everything down with your hands.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot cream cheese delight
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple with juice. Heat to simmering.
Remove from fire.
Add sugar.
Stir to dissolve.
Beat cream cheese
and baby food together.
Add to jello and dissolve completely.
Cool and refrigerate until it mounds.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Shred potatoes and cheese.
Fry potatoes. When brown, sprinkle in cheese slowly as it melts.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate pie no. 2
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add enough water to make a paste. Beat in egg yolks.
Heat remaining water, adding butter and salt. Add vanilla to paste.
Combine ingredients and cook until thick. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Melt butter in large pan and blend in flour.
Stir in the applesauce, soup mix, water, curry powder, ginger and lemon juice. Cook until it thickens to the correct consistency.
Add shrimp and heat thoroughly.
Serve over mounds of rice.
Sprinkle or pass condiments (shredded coconut, ground nuts and chutney). Serves 8.

title: pineapple-cream cheese puffs
directions: Blend softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Mix with Cool Whip. Mix in pineapple and about 2 teaspoons pineapple juice.
Chill for about 20 minutes.

title: nachos and cheese
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add cheese and Ro-Tel.
Best if made in crock-pot and kept warm enough to keep soft.

title: open face reuben sandwiches
directions: Toast bread.
Spread with dressing.
Place corned beef, sauerkraut, mushroom slices and cheese on bread, in that order. Put in toaster oven or broiler until cheese is melted.

title: billy's favorite cabbage and rutabagas
directions: Wash and cut cabbage.
Wash, peel and cut up rutabagas.
Fill pot with water just above vegetables.
Add fatback.
Stirring occasionally, cook until tender.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix together soup and rice and put in dish.
Lay chicken pieces on top and push into mixture.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: spicy apple muffins
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Combine and add to dry ingredients, remaining ingredients.
Mix only until all flour is moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine Karo, water, salt and sugar in a saucepan; boil to 265°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, and gradually beat in the boiling mixture; whit until it begins to stiffen.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat again until cooled somewhat.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper smeared with margarine.

title: sunday beef roast
directions: Line a large Pyrex pan with foil.
Cut roast into thin pieces; put in pan.
Peel, wash and slice potatoes.
Place with roast.
Mix together water, Dale's and season salt.
Pour over roast and potatoes.
Cook at 250° for 4 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well for 4 minutes.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) layer pans for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sub salad
directions: Make salad from first five ingredients.
Combine the last six ingredients and shake well for dressing.
Put dressing on salad just before serving.

title: dana's dip
directions: Brown ground meat and sausage; drain well.
Chunk cheese and melt.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and mushroom soup.
Cook a few minutes over low heat.
Serve with chips.

title: banana punch
directions: Take 4 cups sugar and 6 cups water.
Boil and cool.
Mash bananas and use juice of fruit.
Mix with sugar-water mixture and freeze. Add 2 quarts ginger ale when ready to serve. Frozen mixture will be slushy and be sure to allow a long while in freezer to set up.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini in 1/2-inch slices.
Simmer in water for 10 minutes.
Place in an 8-inch casserole.
Combine the sour cream, Cheddar cheese, butter and salt; heat until blended.
Pour over zucchini.
Combine bread crumbs and grated cheese; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put potatoes on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then add onions and oleo, then salt and pepper.
Heat soups, milk, sour cream and cheese until melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Then put on topping of corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french potato salad
directions: Set aside potatoes to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chopped potatoes.
Let stand in refrigerator for several hours to blend flavors.

title: salad dressing(good for chinese chicken salad)
directions: Blend all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: easy caramel popcorn
directions: In large shallow roasting pan combine popcorn and nuts.
Place in 250° oven while preparing glaze.

title: pat's cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in a chopped walnut or pecan mixture.

title: low cholesterol carrot cake
directions: Mix the rest of it and add to the carrot mixture. Stir just to combine.
Divide between 2 oiled loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese roll
directions: Combine all but 1/2 of chopped beef. Roll cheese ball in remaining beef.
Refrigerate until set.

title: mexican chocolate
directions: Combine milk, cinnamon, salt and coffee in a saucepan and heat to almost boiling.
Strain.
Dissolve chocolate in boiling water and add to milk mixture.
Heat to boiling point.
Add vanilla and pour over marshmallow in each cup.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; add vanilla.
Add bananas, then dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix soup, milk and pepper in 2 quart greassed casserole dish.
Stir in beans,
Sprinkle with the onions.
Bake uncovered 30 - 40 minutes or until hot in the center.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Layer rest of vegetables in order given.
Mix sugar with mayonnaise and spread over top like frosting.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: scripture cake
directions: Turn cake batter into greased and floured 9-inch loaf pan and bake at 325° for 40 minutes; cover with foil and bake 50 minutes longer.
Allow cake to cool 10 minutes before removing from pan. Brush cake with wine or orange juice.
Wrap in foil and store in refrigerator.

title: crunchy cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in all other ingredients, except peanuts.
Cover and chill several hours. Form into ball; roll in nuts to cover.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry pie filling
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thickened, will not be very thick.
Add jello.
Let cool, then add fresh strawberries. In baked pie shell, spread cream cheese, then pour cooled strawberry filling over top.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: creme de menthe squares
directions: Bottom:
In saucepan, combine 1/2 cup margarine and cocoa. Heat and stir until blended. Remove from heat. Add 1/2 cup powdered sugar, egg and vanilla. Stir in cracker crumbs.
Press in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix milk and Bisquick and drop small spoonfuls into a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Roll each piece to cover with sweets. Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook (boil) potatoes until fork-tender.
Peel while hot.
Add margarine to hot potatoes.
Beat in milk, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes until center is set.
Set oven at 350°.

title: better than sex cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, bake cake according to directions. Meanwhile, combine pineapple with its own juice and sugar in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick and syrupy, about 20 minutes.
When cake is done, remove from oven and pierce top with fork at 1-inch intervals. Pour pineapple mixture over cake and spread evenly.
Cool completely.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, oil and eggs together, pour into flat 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 casserole dish. Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over melted margarine. Do not stir! Pour fruit over top. Do not mix! Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serving 175 calories.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from beans.
Cook in boiling water and Wesson oil for 20 minutes.
Drain and
sprinkle with Accent.
Mix beans, soup and pepper together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with fried onions and bake 5 minutes more.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Mix orange juice, sugar, and cornstarch. Cook over medium heat until thick. Pour over carrots and let stand a short time. Serve hot.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin and water.
Blend by hand.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, well-greased. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: great chocolate candy
directions: Mix all and bring to a boil.
When it begins to boil, add 1 tablespoon vinegar.
When mixture forms a soft ball in cold water, remove from stove and place under electric mixer.
When this begins to thicken, add salt, vanilla and butter.
Continue to beat at high speed until mixture is very thick.
Remove and stir in two cups of nuts and press on marble slab.
Be sure the content will stand alone before you pour out of boiler.
Cut in squares.

title: heath bits pecan pie
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9-inch ready crust pie shell with Heath bits.
In mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Mix well and add pecans.
Pour mixture over Heath bits in the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until filling doesn't stick to a knife.

title: chicken and okra gumbo (soup)
directions: Cook chicken in water for 30 to 45 minutes, until tender. Remove chicken from broth; bone and cube.

title: wonder salad
directions: Mix jello and water; add cream cheese.
Stir until dissolved or until it's very small pieces.
Add all other ingredients and refrigerate, stirring every 15 minutes until ice cream is blended in evenly.

title: easy turkey pot pie
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package using 1 1/2 cups water.
Press gently into greased 1-quart ring mold and keep warm. Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add boiling water to liquid to make 1 cup; add bouillon cube and stir until dissolved.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add mushrooms and onion and cook until lightly browned.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add measured liquid, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and stir until thickened and smooth.
Add turkey and heat thoroughly.
Just before serving, unmold stuffing ring onto serving platter.
Spoon turkey mixture around base and into center of ring.
Makes 6 servings.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Combine minced chicken and creamed corn; set aside.
In a large saucepan, heat oil and sherry to just below boiling. Immediately add chicken broth and stir to mix.
Bring mixture to a boil and add chicken and corn mixture.
Add salt to taste.

title: "banana pudding" ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together in churn.
Churn as directed, layering rock salt and ice all the way to the top. (Takes about 30 to 40 minutes.)

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients.
Batter is extremely runny.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured tube pan.
Also makes about 4 dozen cupcakes. Cake takes about 5 minutes to mix!

title: sugar-free angel food cake
directions: Buy already made angel food cake.
About 1 1/2-inch from top of cake, slice top off of cake and place aside.
Cut completely around inside of cake about 1-inch from outside of cake, but not all the way to the bottom of the cake.
Do same thing on inside of cake. Make pudding, pour into hollowed out angel food cake and replace cake top.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: cucumber onion salad
directions: Thickly slice cucumbers and onions in rings.
Cover with salad dressing.
Chop garlic and add to mixture.
Serve and enjoy.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt fat or butter.
Add flour and stir until well blended (do not brown).
Pour on gradually the chicken stock, milk and cream while stirring constantly (add one at a time).
Saute mushrooms in 1 tablespoon of butter (or more) for 5 minutes.
Have chicken and pimentos cut in desired size pieces.
Bring mixture to boiling point (bubbling) and add salt, remaining butter (about 1 tablespoon), chicken, mushroom pieces and pimentos (also green pepper or green peas).
Bring to boiling point and add slightly beaten egg yolks.

title: sauerkraut
directions: *For large container, use 1/2 pound (1 cup) pickling salt to 20 pounds chopped cabbage.
After cured, put in jars and process.

title: crabmeat on cucumber slices
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Spread on cucumber slices.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash and pare potatoes, then grate and mix with salt and onion.
Stir in eggs and add flour.
Have the shortening sizzling hot in frying pan.
Drop a spoonful of batter into pan.
Brown on one side, then turn and brown on the other side.

title: deviled chicken breasts(low-fat)
directions: Place breadcrumbs and chicken in plastic bag and shake.
Heat oil in nonstick skillet and add chicken.
Cook 3 minutes on each side until browned.
Add wine and next 3 ingredients.
Cover, reduce heat and cook 15 minutes.
Remove chicken and mushrooms with slotted spoon.
Add lemon juice and mustard to skillet and stir. Cook 2 minutes.
Pour on top of chicken and serve.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Saute green pepper and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Make a paste of flour and cold chicken broth.
Add this to green pepper and mushroom mixture.
Blend.
Add hot milk until thickened and smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat in make-shift double boiler.
Serve on toast.

title: chicketti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed for casseroles.
Mix other ingredients, except 1/2 of the cheese. Fold mixture into the spaghetti. Pour into a
1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with the remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until bubbly.

title: 2 minute fudge
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together until partially blended.
Put butter over top
in center
of
dish.	Microwave on High for 2 minutes or until
milk feels
warm
on
bottom of dish.
Stir vigorously until
smooth. If	all
butter
has not melted in cooking, it will
as it is stirred.
Blend in nuts.
Pour out on plate and chill for 1 hour. Cut into squares and serve.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand and serve warm.

title: bean casserole
directions: Combine beans and soup.
Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan (I use a large casserole dish).
Before baking, put on Topping.

title: cheese bites
directions: Grate cheeses and combine.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Spread 1/2 of cheese in pan.
Spread chilies over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and flour.
Pour evenly over all.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove from oven and let stand 3 to 5 minutes before cutting into small squares to serve.

title: spaghetti chicken casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti, let cool.
Boil whole chicken or use pieces of chicken equal to approximately 1 whole chicken.
One whole chicken will give you approximately 3 cups of chicken.
Cool and dice. Brown onion, green pepper and mushrooms in butter.
Place in large mixing bowl the ingredients along with the broth, soup and red pimentos plus grated Jack cheese.
Put in large 9 x 16-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saut onion and celery in margarine. Mix all ingredients, adding salt and pepper to taste. (May add red pepper flakes to taste.) Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lush dessert
directions: Mix as pie crust. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch
pan (buttered). Bake at 350° until light brown. Cool completely.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, nuts and margarine.
Spread evenly in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir often.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: In bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg, orange juice and peel; stir into dry ingredients just until blended.
Add cranberries and walnuts.
Spoon into a greased and floured 8 x 4 x 2 inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 - 70 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely. 1 Loaf.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Combine biscuit mix and sugar.
Add banana and water alternately, stirring after each addition.
Stir in shortening and vanilla.
Bake in a greased cupcake pan or paper cups for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain.
Run cold water over spaghetti.
Cut vegetables in small pieces.
Add the salad seasoning.
Add the Italian dressing.
Toss and chill at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: salad with tuna
directions: Cook rice per directions.
Mix rice with the remaining ingredients.
This can be served hot or cold.
You can substitute any vegetable that you wish in this dish.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a bowl, cream together sugar and shortening or margarine.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Divide dough into 4 balls.
Roll one ball at a time out onto floured board.
With floured rolling pin, roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until very light brown. Remove from oven.
Place on rack to cool.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting, if desired.
May add food coloring to frosting for the holidays.

title: chocolate waffle cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto each section of a waffle iron.
Bake 55 seconds.
Don't overbake.
Frost with any frosting.
Freezes well.

title: country butter
directions: Put together in mixer and whip until thoroughly blended.
You can add a pinch of salt, if desired.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Blend coconut, pecans, condensed milk, butter and powdered sugar and roll into small balls about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Chill in refrigerator one hour or longer.
Insert toothpicks into each ball and dip in chocolate paraffin mixture that has been melted over low heat in top of double boiler.
Put on wax paper to dry.

title: mulled cider
directions: Simmer apple cider, 2 cinnamon sticks, whole cloves and granulated sugar for 30 minutes.
Discard cinnamon sticks and cloves, then pour into a heatproof serving bowl.
Add several small apples studded with cloves (they'll float).
Serve hot cider in mugs with cinnamon stick stirrers.
Serves 8.

title: sunken treasure dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well, except for cheeses.
Place in baking dish and top with the cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Keep warm and serve with nacho or tortilla chips.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter, milk and cocoa to a boil; boil hard for 1 minute. Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Drop on wax paper until cool.

title: baked fish casserole
directions: Season fillets with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with chopped onions and cheese slices.
Mix together sour cream and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour on top of cheese slices.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger.
Drain.
Add onions, chilies, soups and sour cream.
Spray pan with oil.
Layer with tortillas and meat mixture.
Top with olives and cheese.
Layer 3-inches deep.
Heat in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Excellent to freeze.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes to heat through.

title: super potato pancakes(german)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls into 1/2 inch
hot
oil
(preferably
an
electric frypan at 375°). Turn when brown.
Serve with sour cream or catsup.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Put sugar, cornstarch
and
water
in saucepan and cook until creamy.
Remove from heat; add a small package strawberry Jell-O gelatin.
Put
cut
up
strawberries
in cooked deep dish pie shell;
pour
all ingredients over berries.
Add Cool Whip or ice cream when serving.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken and save broth for cooking spaghetti.
Cook spaghetti in broth and add margarine.
Saute pepper, celery and onion until tender.
Add chili powder and soups.
Heat thoroughly and add chicken.
Heat and add spaghetti.
Grate cheese on top. Heat in 350° oven until cheese is melted and dish is thoroughly heated.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck and onion.
Add other ingredients and simmer about 1 hour.
Serve with sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions; drain.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stuff manicotti.
Arrange in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layering thin layer of sauce, then manicotti and another layer of sauce.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, until hot.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and reserve 3 tablespoons for topping.
Press remaining mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Mix ice cream, pudding and milk.
Beat until smooth, then pour into cracker crumb shell.
Chill 1 hour. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker mixture reserved from crust.
Serves 12.

title: white grape punch 7rom southern living
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Chill well and stir in club soda just before serving. Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: bean sprout salad
directions: Mix soy sauce and curry powder with mayonnaise.
Mix all ingredients together in a salad bowl and serve.

title: spanakopita spinach-cheese pie(greece)
directions: In a heavy 10 to 12-inch skillet, heat the olive oil over moderate heat until a light haze forms above it.
Add the onions and scallions and stirring frequently, cook 5 minutes or until they are soft and transparent but not brown.
Stir in the spinach; cover tightly.

Cook for 5 minutes, then add the dill, parsley, salt and dash of pepper, stirring and shaking the pan almost constantly. Cook uncovered for about 10 minutes or until most of the liquid in the skillet has evaporated and the spinach has begun to stick lightly to the pan.
Transfer the spinach to a deep bowl and stir in the milk.
Cool to room temperature, then add the cheese and slowly beat in the eggs.
Taste for seasoning.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Season chicken to desired taste with whatever seasoning you prefer (I use Tony's seasoning).
Mix cream of chicken soup, French onion soup and water together.
Put rice in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken evenly on top of rice.
Pour soup mixture over and under the rice, making sure all rice is covered with soup mixture (if not, rice will not cook).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until rice is tender.

title: watermelon cooler
directions: Peel and slice watermelon; cut into pieces in electric blender at high speed.
Liquify 2 cups at a time or process in a food processor.
Add juice and honey, blending until thoroughly mixed. Chill.
Float a slice of lime in each glass.
Serves 12.

title: suzanne's mexican dip
directions: Soften and spread cream cheese in pie dish.
Pour can of Hormel chili over cheese.
Sprinkle on green onions.
Add can of chopped chilies.
Add olives, if desired.
Shake packet of cheese over mixture.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Chop onion and garlic.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread over meat before and/or during grilling.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Stir in flavoring.
Add flour to creamy mixture alternately with milk. Form dough into ball and put into refrigerator for 15 minutes. Take out of refrigerator and shape with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet until lightly brown around edges.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream
sugar,
eggs and oleo.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and cocoa and add alternately with the 2 1/2 cups of zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put sugar,
flour,
cocoa
and 2 cups milk on in double boiler and
bring	to
scalding point.
Beat egg yolks and add other 1/2 cup milk;
stir
into
hot	mixture.
When done, add butter and vanilla.
Pour
into crust.
Top with meringue made from egg whites and brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Put one layer of noodles in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan or baking dish.
Spoon spaghetti sauce over noodles to cover.
(Joanne Engelman's Spaghetti Sauce).
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over sauce. Layer Mozzarella cheese over this.
Put another layer of noodles over this and cover same as previously listed until pan is full. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Layer of cheese should be on top.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain juice off of pineapple and oranges.
Put all ingredients in medium to large bowl and fold together until mixed thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or until chilled.

title: cream of onion soup
directions: Saute butter and onions until tender.
Mix flour and chicken broth and add to onion mixture.
Add milk, water and other ingredients.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Before serving, garnish with chopped peanuts.
Serves 6.

title: grape salad
directions: Soften cheese; blend in mayonnaise.
Beat in juice.
Add marshmallows and pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream and grapes. Put in oblong pan; cut in squares.
Make a day ahead so salad will set up.
Serve with small crackers.

title: cranberry jewel salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and set aside to cool.
Put raw cranberries and orange (quartered and seeds removed) through food chopper.
Add sugar and mix well.
When gelatin begins to thicken, fold in cranberry-orange mix.
Pour into large mold or individual smaller molds and chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place egg whites, sugar, salt, water and corn syrup in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water and beat constantly with a large double rotary beater or electric mixer at high speed until frosting will stand in peaks, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat. Beat in vanilla.
Quickly spread on cake.
Makes enough frosting for top and sides of two 9-inch layer cakes or 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne; drain.
Combine the next 7 ingredients; mix. Stir in chicken.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer mixture, lasagne and cheese, 3 layers each.
Cover; bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves better if it sits 10 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: In large baking pan (greased), layer fish.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Sprinkle with cheese if you wish to.
Crush crackers; mix with oleo.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° until cooked.
Use no salt and pepper.

title: crusty cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Heat 9-inch cast-iron pan (if available) with oil for 5 minutes.
Drain off oil and pour in cornbread mixture.
Bake until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In
mixer
bowl,
cream
together
sugar
and butter or margarine
until
light
and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating
well
after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beating after
each addition.
Add extracts and vanilla; beat well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at	350° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool 15	minutes; remove
from
pan.	When cool, frost or sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Take off bone and cut into small pieces.
Combine cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and chicken broth.
Add stuffing, salt, pepper and margarine; stir well.
Add onion and sour cream.
Pour mixture over pieces of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef dip
directions: Cut beef into bite-size pieces.
Blend all ingredients except nuts in large bowl.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: mothers chicken, rice and peas casserole
directions: Brown onion slightly in butter, Add chicken, peas, and water. Bring to boil. Add rice and cover pot. Turn heat down as low as possible. Add seasoning to your taste and the rest of ingredients when water is gone, approximately 5 minutes.

title: fruited oatmeal bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray loaf pan (8 x 4 x 3-inches) with butter or nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine egg, buttermilk and brown sugar.
Add flour, baking soda and salt, stirring to blend.
Add oats, dates and nuts.
Stir well, turn into pan.
Bake 40 or 45 minutes or until brown and firm to touch. Makes one loaf.

title: chocolate walnut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt margarine.
Add cocoa, stir until smooth.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, water and eggs; beat well.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla, flavoring and walnuts.
Pour in pastry shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in flour and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Place in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave swedish meatballs
directions: Combine beef, eggs, bread crumbs, 1/4 cup milk, onion, parsley, salt, allspice and pepper.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch meatballs.

title: ranch steak
directions: Mix dressing mix, water and oil.
Grill steak for 4 minutes. Brush half on top and grill 3 minutes longer.
Turn and grill for 4 minutes.
Brush on remaining mixture.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry cream roll
directions: In a medium bowl, stir ice cream
with a spoon to soften. Stir in sour cream or yogurt and 2 tablespoons of the liqueur. Cover and return to freezer for 4 to 5 hours or until firm.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil with electric mixer until fluffy. Sift dry ingredients (flour, soda, salt and cinnamon); then put with first mixture.
Add vanilla, pecans, apples and coconut.
Mix into first mixture by hand and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Fold in apples.
Bake at 350°.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Mix cream cheese, onion, cucumber, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Spread onto bread to make sandwiches.
Quarter sandwiches into small triangles and serve.

title: jean worley's corn bread
directions: Beat eggs with milk; add the cooled melted butter and remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 12 x 8-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: hoska bread
directions: Stir the first 6 ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Heat to lukewarm the water and margarine.
Pour lukewarm mixture into the first 6 ingredients; beat for 2 minutes.
Add the eggs and 1/2 cup unsifted flour; beat 2 more minutes.
Add about 3 more cups unsifted flour, stirring in to make fairly stiff dough which should be moist.
Knead about 10 minutes, then cover with plastic wrap and let dough rest in a pan for 1/2 hour.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix together.
Slice cake while still warm and pour glaze over cake.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix together chicken, celery, soups, onion, mayonnaise, lemon juice, water chestnuts, and egg noodles.
Put in greased casserole.
Spread on top corn flakes mixed with melted margarine. Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 8.
Freezes well.

title: cole slaw
directions: Remove core of cabbage and cut head into eighths.
Put enough of the cabbage into the container of your blender to fill one half.
Add water to cover cabbage.
Press chop button for approximately 5 seconds, or until coarsely chopped throughout. Empty into strainer to drain thoroughly.
Repeat with remaining cabbage and the other vegetables until all are chopped.
Drain very well in a colander.
Place vegetables in a bowl.

title: chicken crescent almandine
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients and cook until hot and bubbly. Put in ungreased 8 x 13-inch pan.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions.
When done, take a wooden spoon handle and poke holes into top of cake. Pour caramel topping on top of cake while still hot.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crush candy bars and sprinkle on top of Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: raisin bran coffee cake square
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine milk, honey and eggs; add to flour mixture.
Add oil; stir just to moisten.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups cereal.
Add spices.
Pour batter into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: cold pennies(carrots)
directions: Pare and slice carrots. Boil in salted water until tender. Drain and let cool slightly.
Sprinkle onion and pepper over carrots in dish.

Make topping for carrots by bringing the tomato juice, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and garlic powder to a boil. Pour over carrots and chill. This dish is better after marinating overnight in refrigerator. Drain before placing in serving dish. Serve cold.
Yields 10 servings.

title: jiffy cake dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, except bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Add pudding and remaining milk.
Beat until smooth and thick.
Pour pudding mixture over cake.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and/or coconut.
Top with whipped topping and additional nuts and/or coconut.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 400° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: nut and fruit cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Let oatmeal stand in boiling water while you mix the rest of the ingredients. Add oatmeal. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cut tortillas in 1/2 and lightly fry.
Mix soup, chicken, sour cream, onion and chili peppers together.

title: sugar-free chocolate pudding
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Mix in sweetener equal to 3/4 cup sugar.

title: ham-cheese oven omelette
directions: Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into greased oblong baking dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch) or an 8 x 8-inch square baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini with other vegetables and salt.
Allow to stand 4 hours or overnight.
Drain.
Rinse and drain again. Press out excess liquid.
Combine vegetables and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat and boil gently for 20 minutes. Ladle into hot jars.
Process in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Yields 8 pints.

title: tea ring
directions: Cut refrigerated biscuits in quarters.
Place 4 tablespoons butter in round cake dish; microwave 1 minute and 30 seconds on High or until butter is melted.
Immediately stir the brown sugar and cinnamon into melted butter.
Add biscuit quarters, 1/4 at a time; stir to coat with mixture.
Arrange biscuit quarters evenly in dish.
Microwave 4 to 5 minutes on High, or until biscuits are slightly firm to the touch.

title: noodles special
directions: Brown beef, onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Add tomatoes (drain and save juice).
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add juice from tomatoes and mix.

title: icebox cake
directions: Put cream between two layers of vanilla wafers and put Cool Whip on top.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: 6 easy steps to the perfect pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt mixture with a fork or pastry blender until crumbs are coarse and granular.
Add 3 to 6 tablespoons cold water, a little at a time.
Mix quickly and evenly through the flour until the dough just holds together.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, hard-boiled eggs, peas, onion, green pepper and bacon bits in order given.
Seal top with Miracle Whip mixed with sugar.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate 8 to 24 hours.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, except ham and chicken broth. Lower heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Do not drain.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat like mad!

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Pour boiling water over the gelatin.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.	Pour into mold or 8 x 12 Pyrex dish and refrigerate until congealed.

title: borden bake 'n' eat sticks
directions: Roll biscuits into sticks.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes. Serve with salad.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth; stir in the olives and onions.
Spread over ham slices.
Roll up jellyroll style, starting with a short side.
Chill for at least 1 hour (can be made a day ahead).
Just before serving, cut into 1-inch pieces. Yields 40 appetizers.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Combine first 3 items and mix until smooth.
Blend in lemon juice.
Add marshmallows and drained fruit cocktail.
Add sliced bananas and stir everything in.
Put in dish and freeze.
Set out approximately 1/2 hour before serving.

title: chicken breast wraps
directions: Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream in large baking dish.
Prepare chicken breasts for cooking.
Cover each breast with dry beef.
Wrap bacon around it and secure with a toothpick. Place on top of the cream of chicken soup/sour cream.
Cover the top with slivered almonds.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven or until done.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Boil milk and add 1 1/2 cups of sugar.
Slowly add well beaten eggs.
Let cool.
Add the Milnot and whipping cream along with remaining sugar and vanilla to taste.
Chill this mixture completely before freezing in an electric ice cream machine.

title: english toffee
directions: Generously butter cookie sheet and sprinkle 1 1/2 cups chopped nuts over buttered pan.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: Wipe chicken dry; make paste of first 5 ingredients.
Brush to coat chicken evenly.
Stack pieces in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.

title: 25 minute chicken and noodles
directions: In med skillet mix broth, basil, pepper and vegetables. Over med-high heat, heat to a boil. Reduce heat to medium. Cover and cook 5 minutes. Stir in noodles. Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring often. Add chicken and heat through.

title: best ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, vanilla, brown sugar, sugar, water and eggs together.
In another bowl, mix the flour, salt and baking soda. Pour flour mixture into butter mixture and stir until well blended. Add chocolate chips, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Result is soft and chewy cookies.
Makes about 3 to 4 dozen.

title: gardener's lasagna
directions: Place zucchini in an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 11 minutes.
Drain. Place beef and garlic in 1 quart casserole.
Microwave on High 6 minutes.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and Italian seasoning.
Mix cottage cheese, egg and parsley.
Place alternate layers of the mixtures, cheeses and bread crumbs in baking dish. Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on Medium-high for 15 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw 1 loaf of frozen bread dough.
Put 1 teaspoon liquid margarine, 1 teaspoon brown sugar and 1 teaspoon honey in 18 cupcake pans.
Divide dough into 18 balls.
Let raise until over cupcake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn immediately onto foil covered plate.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mince onions.
Combine beef, onions, crumbs, 3/4 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and egg.
In skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Cook meatballs, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove meatballs with slotted spoon.
In skillet, add ketchup, 1/3 cup water, mustard, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce and bring to boil. Return meatballs to pan.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until hot and cooked, 3 to 5 minutes.
Very good.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak the bread which has been broken into small pieces in the milk.
Cream well the butter and sugar and add the eggs, one at a time.
Stir in the vanilla, raisins, pecans and bourbon.
Mix with soaked bread.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Heat oil in large pot over medium heat.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; saute 4 minutes or until onion is softened. Add carrot; cover and cook 2 minutes.
Add zucchini, chili powder, oregano, cumin and cinnamon; saute 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, breaking up with wooden spoon, and salt.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat; simmer, partially covered, 15 minutes.
Stir in all the beans.
Simmer, stirring, until heated through.

title: lasagna(john is famous with our friends and family for his lasagna.)
directions: Saute onions, garlic and celery in olive oil; set aside. Brown meat together; drain fat.
Mix onions, garlic, celery and meat into sauce.

title: matzoh meal pancake
directions: Beat all ingredients with fork.
Melt butter in small frying pan.
Put mixture in melted butter and fry until brown and slightly soft in middle.
Turn with spatula and fry slightly until done.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, oil, sour milk and eggs.
Stir in prunes and all the remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cake is done when tested with toothpick.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and evaporated milk in a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan; bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 238°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat, stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until blended.

title: arroz con pollo(puerto rican chicken)
directions: Cook chicken in water and salt until chicken is tender. Reserve broth.
Fry onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon olive oil until vegetables are cooked.
Set aside in a large bowl.
Fry ham in 1 tablespoon oil until all sides are brown.
Add chicken and ham to bowl with onion and green pepper.
Add olives and stewed tomatoes.

title: french-style green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and bake in greased casserole in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with French fried onions and brown 10 minutes more.
Serves a family of 6.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Place sliced cucumbers in gallon jugs; pour salt over cucumbers, then fill with water.
Let stand for 7 days.
After 7 days, pour this off.
Put 1 teaspoon of alum in each jug, then refill with fresh hot water.
Let this stand overnight; pour off. Mix sugar and vinegar; stir well and pour over pickles.
Pour off and heat 3 mornings.
On the third morning, put pickles in pint jars.
Seal.

title: slumgullion
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, peppers and seasonings.
Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Add to meat mixture in casserole dish.
Stir in tomato soup and 1/2 of cheese.
Mix well.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Just toss a salad and you have a meal.

title: country steak with gravy
directions: Cut meat into about 1 1/2-inch strips. Pound flour into both sides of meat. Brown meat on both sides in about 1/4-inch oil. Drain. Salt and pepper the meat. Pour off and discard remaining oil in frypan and return meat to the pan. Pour over enough water to cover. Bring to a boil. Then reduce heat from medium-low to low and let simmer at least 1/2 hour to 45 minutes until very tender.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix well and mold into 6 medium size patties.
Brown in hot oil for 10 minutes on each side.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruits; add pudding and juices and top with fruit!

title: magnificent chocolate pudding
directions: In bottom of trifle dish or other large glass bowl, layer as follows: vanilla wafers, chocolate pudding, marshmallows and whipped topping. Repeat layers as needed leaving enough whipped topping for a final top layer. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs at high speed in a mixing bowl about 5 minutes.
Add sugar gradually, beating until mixture is light and fluffy. Combine flour and baking powder; add to batter with vanilla and beat at low speed until smooth.
In a saucepan, heat milk and butter just until butter melts, stirring occasionally.
Add to batter, beating until combined.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.
Delicious with strawberries and whipped cream.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Steam broccoli and drain away water. Put in the bottom of a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Take the boiled chicken off the bone and put over broccoli.
(Don't put the skin in.)
Spoon the soup evenly over the chicken.
Put shredded cheese over the soup.
Mix the Stove Top according to directions on the box (use chicken broth instead of water).
Put over the cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until top is crispy.

title: pot roast with vegetables
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper and roll in flour.
Melt shortening in heavy skillet and brown roast slowly and thoroughly. Sprinkle meat with thyme or marjoram and chopped onion.
Add water; cover tightly and cook slowly over low heat for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Turn meat 2 or 3 times during cooking.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook until meat and vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.
To make gravy, thicken juices with flour and water paste.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Roll into balls and bake for 40 minutes at 250°.
Roll in powdered sugar after baking.

title: stove top dressing mix
directions: Mix well, then place in Ziploc bags and freeze.
Makes enough for 4 batches.

title: miracle fruit cake
directions: Combine in saucepan the first six ingredients.
Boil gently 3 minutes.
Cool in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, fruits, peels and nuts.
Sift together flour, spices, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Add gradually to fruit mixture.
Beat well after each addition.

title: wassail
directions: Bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Remove cinnamon.
Serve hot. Makes 4 quarts, 25 cups.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup in Pyrex bowl.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Mix in peanuts.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Mix in vanilla and butter.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Quickly mix in baking soda.
Quickly pour onto buttered cookie sheet and let harden.

title: mints
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add powdered sugar until thick. If mixture is too thick, add milk one teaspoon at a time.
Ad flavoring of your choice and coloring.
Drop or put in mold and then place on wax paper.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice meat across grain in thin 1/4-inch strips.
Season with pepper.
Heat bacon drippings.
Add meat and saute until brown on all sides.
Add onions and saute 5 minutes.
Add consomme.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms and green peppers.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes; simmer 2 minutes. Blend butter and flour to make paste.
Stir into mixture in pan, a little at a time.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Place on preheated platter.
Garnish with parsley. Serve with rice.

title: edna tuxhorn's macaroni and cheese
directions: Add butter, Velveeta cheese, salt and pepper and half and half.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Remove from oven and cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Drizzle melted butter over cracker crumbs and return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: couch-couch
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt, baking powder and milk or water.
Add to hot shortening in skillet over high heat.
Let a crust form.
Give a good stir and lower heat to simmer.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, then add the rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: eggless peanut butter ice cream
directions: Beat all top ingredients well.
Pour into prechilled can. Finish filling with milk or half and half cream.
Freeze according to manufacturer's manual.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Roll out pastry for the bottom of the pan.
In saucepan, boil 3 cups of water.
On the side, mix sugar with cream of tartar. Add to boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add 36 Ritz crackers one by one into boiling water.
Do not stir!
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Cover with second pastry shell, if desired.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients and place in baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
(This is good served hot as a main dish or served cold on a bed of lettuce, or as sandwich filling.)

title: german potato salad
directions: Place in roaster, heat 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: stuffed artichoke bread
directions: Saute onions until tender; add remaining ingredients (except bread) and set aside.
Dig the center of the French bread out until only bosee shell is left.
Place the cheese mixture in shell and spread evenly.
Wrap entire mixture in the bread loaf in foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot with chips or crackers.

title: key lime pie(to make 4 pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Do not overcook.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and bring to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, Marshmallow Fluff, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix quickly as this hardens fast.
Turn into 2 well-greased pans (8 x 8-inches). Allow to set and cut in squares.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Pour pie filling into prepared dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir to form soft dough.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto pie filling to form dumplings.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove cover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: fish chowder
directions: In a heavy kettle, fry pork to a golden brown color.
Add onions and fry to a light yellow color.
Add potatoes; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add water; cook until potatoes are about half done.
Add fish, flesh side down.
Cook until potatoes are done (soft).
Remove any skin from the fish and break the flesh into coarse flakes.
Serve hot.

title: quick barley soup
directions: Bring water to a boil; add bouillon and beef, a pinch at a time.
Simmer 15 minutes; add barley, tomatoes and spices.
Simmer 10 minutes, add potatoes and simmer 15 minutes.
Add vegetables and simmer until all is done.
Taste to adjust seasonings.
Add more water if needed.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together in top of double boiler; add water.
Combine egg yolks with lemon juice and beat.
Add to rest of mixture.
Cook until thick over boiling water for 25 minutes. (This takes care of starchy taste.) Add lemon extract, butter and vinegar.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell. Cover with meringue and brown.

title: all-bran rolls
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over bran and sugar.
Add yeast to the other cup lukewarm water until dissolved.
Add to other ingredients, then eggs.
Add flour and beat thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator overnight or make at 6 for 12 noon.
Roll out, cut and let rise 3 hours.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, orange juice and kool aid.
Add ginger ale.
When ready to serve add sherbet.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Take off the bones and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bring chicken soup and broth to boil and pour over chicken.
Top with flour and sweet milk; mix together.
Add 1 stick margarine (melted).
Pour over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: quesadillas
directions: In a long pan, warm a tortilla (one at a time).
Fold and fill with cheese.
Keep in pan til cheese is melted, turning them over several times.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Cook 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
This will make 2 loaf cakes.

title: chilaquiles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a medium bowl, combine salsa, salsa verde and cilantro.
Mix well. Spread 1/2 cup salsa mixture in the bottom of greased baking dish. Layer half of tortillas, beans, chicken, remaining salsa mixture and cheese in baking dish.
Repeat layering.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant meat into bite size pieces (this will take about two months).
Cut vegetables into cubes (another two months). Place meat in a pan and cover with 1,000 gallons of brown gravy. Simmer for four weeks.
Shovel in salt and pepper to taste.
When meat is tender, add vegetables (a steam shovel or backhoe is useful for this).
Simmer slowly for four more weeks.
Garnish with parsley.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more people are expected, add 2 rabbits.
I do not recommend this however, as very few people like hare in their stew.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Toast sesame seed and almonds in a 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes. Cool and set aside.
Chop the cabbage and green onions. Crush noodles inside package, carefully. Remove flavor packet. Add noodles, sesame seed, almonds and green onions to chopped cabbage.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and season to taste. Drain.
Boil noodles and set to side.
Add sauce to meat and simmer for approximately 5 minutes.
Add Ricotta cheese and continue to simmer.
Put a covering of meat and sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of noodles, sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat
until gone, end with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until cheese browns.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
When hot, add onions and garlic.
Cook until onions are done.
Drain tomatoes.
Cut small into pan.
Add pizza spices, tomato paste and brown sugar.
Stir all ingredients and simmer (not boil) gently for 40 minutes.

title: hershey pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add eggs, one at a time, alternately with flour mixed with soda, salt and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Melt Hershey bars; add syrup.
Add to creamed mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Use a 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan that has been greased and floured.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture may be slightly lumpy, but it doesn't matter.
Pour into 2 lightly greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.
The top of the bread will crack when done.

title: fruit salad
directions: For smaller amount, use 1/2 of each ingredient.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken, pepper, celery and onion in 1 gallon water until meat comes off bone. (Save water.)

Take meat off bone (do not use skin). Dice potatoes and cook (separate). Mash up 1/2 of onion, celery and bell pepper with fork. Add chicken, potatoes, mashed onion, bell pepper and celery, milk and can of milk to the water you cooked the chicken in. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook until hot enough to eat.

title: martha ann's corn pudding
directions: *If using frozen corn, defrost in microwave, then cook 10 minutes before adding to the other ingredients.

title: aunt mary's sweet garlic dill pickles
directions: Sterilize jars.
In each quart jar, place 1/8 teaspoon alum, 1/4 of medium onion, 3 cloves garlic and 2 heads of dill.

title: easy spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches well, reserving 1 1/2 c syrup. In 2 qt bowl, combine reserved syrup, vinegar, all spice, cloves and cinnamon sticks. Microwave 4 to 6 minutes on high or until mixture boils. Reduce setting on microwave. Microwave 4 minutes. Remove and discard cloves.

title: "light baked alaska"
directions: Soften yogurt until it's just soft enough to be pliable. Press yogurt into a bowl with rubber or plastic spatula.
Smooth so it will rest evenly on angel food cake.

title: cold coffee cookies
directions: Combine sugar, Crisco, eggs and coffee.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to coffee mixture.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pralines
directions: Mix all, except pecans, in 2-quart pan; boil over low heat until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Remove; add pecans. Beat until it thickens. Pour by tablespoon on wax paper.

title: claudia grice's crock-pot apple butter
directions: Put cooked apples, sugar and vinegar in slow cooker.
Cover and cook 12 hours on low.
Puree mixture at this stage if lumps are undesired.
Return to cooker.
Add spices and cook 3 hours more on high without lid or until desired consistency is reached. May be frozen or put in sterilized jars and processed in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Golden Delicious apples are especially good for this recipe.
Yields 3 pints.

title: light batter(for deep frying vegetables)
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add water and egg; stir until smooth.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil and peel potatoes.
Melt margarine.
Beat eggs slightly. Mix all ingredients together and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° to 375° until done, about 1 hour. This souffle can be baked in shallow oblong pan.

title: creamy southern pralines
directions: Cook sugars, butter, milk and syrup to soft ball stage or 238° on a candy thermometer.
Add baking powder, vanilla and nuts. Beat until creamy and of a consistency that can be dropped by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set until cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Bring undiluted soup to boil.
Melt cheese in soup.
Dissolve gelatin in water at room temperature.
Add gelatin mixture to soup mixture; let cool.
Add all other ingredients, except shrimp.
Let cool in refrigerator for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and pour into a well-greased mold.

title: bernie's pastry mix
directions: Mix as for pie crust.
Store in refrigerator until needed.

title: polo picante casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions in chicken bouillon. Combine soup, milk, onion, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Layer ingredients in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Layer in chicken, rice, soup mix, picante and cheese.
Repeat layers.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar until fluffy.
Alternate flour and buttermilk until mixed; add flavoring.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Let cheese and sausage warm to room temperature.
Add Bisquick, red pepper and parsley.
Mix with hands thoroughly. Roll into inch size balls.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 375° for 15 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: avocado sour cream dip
directions: In very thin layers in a 9 x 12-inch dish, spread enough to cover each layer.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Cream butter and sugar together; add egg.
Stir creamed mix together with flour mixture, alternating with milk.
Add blueberries.
Pour batter into greased muffin tin and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and butter; beat well.
Add lemon juice and rind, salt and egg yolks; beat well.
Beat egg whites until light and fluffy; fold into sugar mixture.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes more.
Yields a 9-inch pie.

title: mexican artichokes
directions: Artichokes:
Cut off stems at bottom of artichoke, then cut off top stems.
Use
scissors
to
cut off sharp points of remaining
leaves.	 (I
pull
off	the
tough,
bottom
row). Submerge artichokes in
water in a large saucepan and boil for 40 minutes.
(You
can
also microwave them, check your oven's cookbook.) They are done when a leaf can be pulled off easily. Drain upside down and cool.

title: brown rice and bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla together.
Add cinnamon. Stir in rice, bread and raisins.
Bour into 3 quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Pudding is done when knife inserted between edge and center comes out clean.
Let cool to warm!
Great for breakfast and desserts.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine soup and water.
Simmer a few minutes. Arrange buttered bread on a cookie sheet; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil until lightly browned.
Pour soup into bowls.
Top each with a portion of the bread.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: apricot liqueur
directions: Put all ingredients into a 1-quart glass covered container. Cover tightly.
Invert container once a day for 3 weeks.
Remove apricots and save. Strain liquid until clear and place in a glass bottle. Apricots may be frozen to munch on or served with liqueur. Great for the holidays.
Yields 1 pint.
Enjoy!

title: twinkie delight
directions: Layer Twinkies, chocolate pudding, bananas and vanilla pudding, then Cool Whip.

title: crab stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done at 325°; pierce to allow steam to escape. Cut potatoes in half; remove insides. Whip with butter, cream, salt, pepper, onion and cheese. Mix in drained and flaked crab meat. Refill potato shells and sprinkle with paprika. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: french meatballs and spaghetti
directions: Mix meat,
eggs, crackers, milk, bell pepper, onion, celery and garlic powder.
Make into meatballs about 1/2 the size of your fist.
Roll in all purpose flour and brown in small amount of olive oil in a skillet. Brown all sides of meat balls lightly. Remove and place in pot of sauce.

title: potato and cheddar soup
directions: Bring water to a boil in large saucepan.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Measure 1 cup, adding water, if necessary.

title: delicious baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook elbows in salted water.
Set aside in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In double boiler, melt butter.
Add mustard, onion, salt, pepper and flour.
Stir.
Add milk, stirring often, until hot.
Cut up cheese into strips and add to milk (save about 1/4 cup of the cheese for top).
Stir until melted.
Pour over drained macaroni.
Stir so all are covered with cheese.

title: aunt bea's sponge cake and frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs; add sugar and mix well.
Blend all dry ingredients and add alternately with the hot milk to the egg mixture.
Add vanilla and pour into pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Top with the following frosting.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco and sugar well.
Add egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Add coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Use 2 or 3 round cake pans.

title: lacy edged corn cakes
directions: Put all in bowl and beat with electric mixer 1 1/2 to 2 minutes at top speed.
If mixed by hand, beat eggs before adding.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Add oil to egg and beat.
Mix ingredients in blender or electric mixer for 15 minutes.
Brush on chicken while cooking. This is also good on pork chops on the grill.
Extra sauce may be stored in the refrigerator for 3 weeks.
You may also make half a recipe using 1 egg.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread coconut and nuts in pan.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour over nuts.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak in thin strips. Melt butter and brown meat, saute' onions add rest of the ingredients except sour cream. Cook about 20 min. Just before serving add sour cream and serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream the margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, soda and buttermilk alternately with sugar and shortening mixture.
Add vanilla and coconut. Bake in three 9-inch pans for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: onion biscuit squares
directions: Heat oven to 450°; grease square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
In skillet, cook onions; stir in 1/4 teaspoon each of salt and pepper, in hot shortening until onions are tender and golden.
Set aside. Prepare dough.
Roll dough to a 10-inch square; pat firmly over bottom and sides of pan; spread onions over top.
In a small bowl, beat egg, sour cream and 1/4 teaspoon salt; pour over onions.
Bake about 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cut into squares and serve warm with roast beef.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: spice tea
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Steep 15 minutes, then remove and add the juices and sugar.
After making, leave tea on simmer.
Do not boil again.

title: banana pepper spread
directions: Blend peppers and mix in a big pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes.
In another bowl, mix flour and water.
Pour flour and water in slowly until thick.

title: meringue
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar and beat until well mixed and fluffy.
Spread evenly over pie filling, making dips and curls.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: deep dish pan pizza
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Chop all vegetables.
Simmer in with hamburger.
Add tomato paste and sauce.
Simmer about 15 minutes. Coat large casserole dish with oil.
Press biscuits into bottom until it is completely covered, even the sides.
Biscuits should be flattened out about 1/2-inch thick.
Fill with cooked meat and vegetables.
Top with both cheeses.
Bake until biscuits are brown.

title: 7 layer dip "tex mex"
directions: Mash avocados with lemon, salt and pepper.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together.
Layer in a 1/2-inch deep oblong pan in the following order:
bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 225° for 2 hours and 45 minutes.

title: tomato flip
directions: Sterilize 4 to 6 jelly jars.
Keep hot.

title: baklava
directions: Lightly butter bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Layer 9 sheets of filo dough with butter between layers.
Spread 1 cup of nut mixture (sugar, nuts and cinnamon) on top layer.
Sprinkle with butter. Layer 4 sheets of filo dough with butter between each layer and spread 1 cup nut mixture on top layer.
Repeat 4 layers of buttered filo dough and nut mixture on top 5 more times.
The last layer of filo dough is 9 sheets with butter between layers.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Cook rice in boiling water until tender.
Drain; add seasonings, butter or margarine and meat.
Shape the mixture into small rolls.
Wrap a leaf of the cabbage around each meat ball. The cabbage leaves have been wilted in boiling water for about 5 minutes.
Place the wrapped rolls in a kettle; add tomato juice and cover.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; add juices.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and cut up apples.
Place in a greased pie pan.
Cover with cinnamon.
Mix together other ingredients and cover apples. Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
