directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add warm water.
Cook over medium heat, like pudding, stirring constantly.
Serve hot with butter over hot biscuits.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes (peel first) in boiling salted water and drain. Mash until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Cover and refrigerate.
May be used anytime in 2 weeks.

title: minute caramel frosting
directions: Boil brown sugar, cream and butter for 3 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add vanilla.
Beat to proper consistency.
Good on banana cake.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and bell pepper; drain.
Cook rice.
Add corn, soup and rice.
Mix all together in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rainbow slices
directions: Line 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with wax paper.
Beat butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and powder until well blended.
Divide into thirds.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Cut up onion and saute it in butter in skillet.
Add the pork and heat it until the pork starts to brown.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir well to prevent sticking to pan.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: breakfast casserole(sausage and egg)
directions: Brown and crumble sausage.
Drain off grease.
Can also rinse sausage in hot water to remove additional fat.
In a blender or mixing bowl, combine eggs, milk, salt and dried mustard until just blended.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
This makes two pies.

title: ginger's rum cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well at least 4 or 5 minutes. (Soak nuts in rum while mixing batter.)
Mix about 2 tablespoons batter into nut mixture before adding to cake mixture; it keeps nuts from settling to bottom of cake.
Fold nut mixture into cake batter very gently without excessive mixing.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread(grandma's favorite)
directions: Combine oil, eggs, water and sugar; sift together the flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and other spices.
Add pumpkin and blend until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in raisins and nuts last.
Makes 3 loaves.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: barbecue with 7-up
directions: Cut fat from roast.
Place meat in crock-pot.
Mix barbecue sauce and 7-Up.
Pour over roast.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or until meat can be broken apart into small pieces.

title: crisp noodle chicken
directions: Place cut up chicken in singe layer in a 1-quart casserole. In bowl, combine soup, sour cream, onion soup mix and pepper; blend thoroughly.
Spread over chicken; sprinkle with noodles. Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: easy rocky road
directions: Microwave Directions:
Butter 8-inch square pan.
In large microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate chips, butter and shortening. Microwave at Medium 5 to 7 minutes or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred.
Add marshmallows and nuts; blend well.
Spread evenly into prepared pan, cover and chill until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: cabbage creole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain.
Combine regular tomatoes, Ro-Tel tomatoes, Cheddar cheese soup and 1 head cabbage.
Simmer 1 hour uncovered.
Serve with cornbread.

title: italian turkey casserole
directions: Pour the water into a large saucepan and add the salt.
Bring to a boil and gradually add cornmeal, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon.
Cook over medium heat until the mixture is the consistency of mashed potatoes (about 30 minutes).
Put into a 10-inch square buttered baking dish and level off with a spoon. Spoon the sausage and turkey over the pollinate layer.
Saute the mushrooms in the butter and lay on top of turkey.
Spread the tomato sauce over all.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy oven beef stew and noodles
directions: In 3-quart casserole dish, combine meat, soup, soup mix and water.
Mix well.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Drain and toss with butter.
To serve, spread noodles on large serving plate and top with stew.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil until thick.
Make a pan of homemade biscuits and enjoy - very delicious.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together.
Store in a tightly covered jar.
Mix 2 to 3 heaping teaspoons into a cup of hot or cold water.
Great for those chilly winter nights or hot summer days!

title: chicken ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in freezer for 10 minutes. Form into ball and roll in nuts.
Serve with party crackers.

title: baked french toast
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, mix and melt brown sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam and pour butter and sugar mixture into dish.
Mix eggs, milk and vanilla. Arrange slices of bread in baking dish and pour egg mixture over bread.
Use all of the mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dijon ham and lentil soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients, except mustard. Heat to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour. Stir in mustard. Serve hot!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain all liquid from beans.
Put in bowl with undiluted consomme and let soak at least 1 hour.
Broil mushrooms in butter; add to beans.
(One large can mushrooms can be substituted for fresh ones.)
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix together the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, salt, lemon pepper and thyme.
Dip chicken into margarine, then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook the hen or fryers.
Remove meat from bones.
Melt oleo. Add green pepper, celery, green onion and garlic.
Cook spaghetti in 7 cups of broth until tender.
Add chicken, vegetable mixture, soup and pimentos.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese. Heat until cheese melts.

title: mush in a pan
directions: Cook onion and okra in the butter until tender and done. Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add stewed tomatoes and simmer.

title: crusty coconut pie
directions: Pour milk over coconut; let set 5 minutes. Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Add milk, coconut and vanilla flavoring. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Yield: 6 servings.

title: crepes
directions: Combine all ingredients. Beat well. Heat greased skillet. Remove from heat. Spoon 2 tablespoons of batter. Lift and tier skillet to spread batter. Return to heat. Brown one side only. Remove from pan and place on paper towel.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix shortening with flour.
Gradually add milk.
Knead a minute or so and turn out on floured board.
Roll dough thin, approximately 1/8-inch thick and in rectangular shape.
Spread sausage on dough and roll as for jelly roll.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: slumgullion
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Spray nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Heat 1 minute.
Stir-fry chicken in 2 batches until browned.
Remove. Remove skillet from heat; spray skillet with cooking spray. Stir-fry vegetables until tender-crisp.
Add soup, water, soy and ginger; heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet; heat through. Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 325°.
Serve hot with your favorite crackers.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Pop enough popcorn to make 5 or 6 quarts.
Spray a brown paper bag with Pam and put popped corn in bag.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Chop vegetables in bite-size pieces.
Layer all ingredients in order given.
Seal with foil.
Bake 4 hours at 250°.
Use a large roaster pan.
Makes a large amount.

title: basic butter cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until smooth and fluffy.
Mix dry ingredients together; add dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at low speed for first 1/2 minute.
Add flour mixture a little at a time. Add milk, vanilla and 1 egg; beat 2 minutes.
Stop mixer; add 3 eggs and beat 1 minute at low speed.
Pour in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° until done.
Spread favorite frosting or Creamy Deluxe Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, milk and bring to a boil.
Cook 4 minutes, stirring frequently to prevent scorching.	Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until ready to pour. Put in a buttered dish and cut when cooled.
This recipe works well when doubled and put in a buttered 8 x 8 Pyrex dish.
Also cooks better in a heavy pan.

title: vanilla rolled cookies
directions: Beat butter, eggs and sugar until well blended.
Add vanilla and stir.
Combine dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Place bowl in refrigerator for 1 hour. Remove and divide dough in 2 parts and roll each into a 1 1/2-inch diameter roll. Wrap in waxed paper and put in refrigerator.
When ready, slice and bake in 350° oven on cookie sheet.
You may decorate in any manner.

title: not enough pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan. Punch holes in cake with wooden spoon handle. Pour pineapple with juice over cake. Let cool. Mix pudding with 2 1/2 cups milk. Add cream cheese; beat until stiff. Spread over pineapple. Add layer of Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate.

title: plains cheese ring(via rosalyn carter)
directions: Combine all ingredients except preserves.
Season to taste with peppers.
Mix well and place in a 5 or 6-cup, lightly-greased ring mold.
Refrigerate until firm, several hours or overnight. To serve, unmold and fill center with preserves.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: good pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and lard.
Mix egg, water and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture.
Makes 3 crusts.

title: shredded yams
directions: Shred yams in a gallon of water.
Add 1 tablespoon of salt. Drain and wash well.
Put in glass baking dish that is 12 x 6 x 3-inches.
Mix sugar, syrup and water and cook until a simple syrup has been formed.
Add margarine.
Pour pineapple juice over shredded yams, then the syrup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until they are transparent in color.

title: microwave baked butternut squash
directions: Pare squash.
Cut in 1/2-inch thick slices and remove seeds. Arrange slices in a 2-quart glass baking dish.
Sprinkle water over squash and dot with butter.
Cook, covered, 10 to 12 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Add salt and pepper, stir to blend.
Rest, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cherry pecan pie
directions: Drain cherries and mash in strainer.
Beat milk and cherries, add lemon juice and rind.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: In large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients.
Add next 4 items. Mix gently.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes nearly 2 quarts.
Use within a week.

title: harvest corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter.
Add corn, potatoes, soup and mushrooms.
Stir in milk and water.
Add peppers; season with salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Serve and garnish with bacon. Yields approximately 12 servings.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: mystery pudding
directions: Mix all together lightly (do not beat).
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° in a greased pan.
Top with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: chicken-stuffing casserole
directions: Cook chicken, remove meat from bones and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Cook vegetables according to directions on package.
Make stuffing according to directions on package.
Put 1/2 stuffing in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients and spread on stuffing.
Top with other half of stuffing.
Spread cheese on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut patty candy
directions: Mix together, heat to 260°.
Remove from heat, add red food coloring, 2 tablespoons butter or oleo, 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar. Pour onto large cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Combine coconut, chocolate and butterscotch chips and nuts.
Pour over top of crumbs.
Pour milk over top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate on low heat.
Cool.
In a bowl, cream together sugar and butter.
Add cooled chocolate. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating mixture on high speed for 5 minutes after each addition.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell. Top with Cool Whip and slivered or shaved chocolate pieces.

title: lady diana's peanuts
directions: Add peanuts to egg white mixture. Put in jelly roll pan.
Stir every 10 minutes in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool on waxed paper.
Store in can. These peanuts are great!

title: country apple dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg at low speed until crumbly. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread with pie filling. Combine brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Finely chop shrimp and set aside.
Combine all other ingredients and mix well. Add shrimp to mixture and serve with crackers or vegetables.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and brown sugar.
Stir in eggs and buttermilk. Add combined dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon 2 inches apart on a baking sheet which has been rubbed with Crisco.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 10 dozen 1 1/2-inch cookies.

title: spicy sauce penne
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the sauce, olives, pine nuts, capers, anchovies and parsley.
Simmer 15 minutes and toss with the cooked pasta.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn souffle or corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and place in 2 1/2-quart greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
If desired, add 3 tablespoons sugar.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In Dutch oven, combine chicken, 8 cups water, onion, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer. Cook and cover until chicken is tender, about 1 hour.
Remove chicken.
Cool slightly.
Remove and discard skin and bones.
Cut meat into bite size pieces.
With slotted spoon, remove onion and bay leaves; skim fat from broth.
Add remaining 6 cups of water, chicken, celery, carrots, bouillon, basil and parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer covered just until carrots are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add noodles.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes stirring occasionally.

title: corn 'n squash pudding
directions: In separate pans, cook squash and corn according to package directions.
Drain corn; set vegetables aside.
In a small skillet, cook onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown. Remove from heat.
Combine eggs, milk, sugar, salt and pepper. Stir in onion mixture.
Add stuffing mix, squash and drained corn, stirring until combined.
Turn mixture into a 10 x 6 x 2 baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until knife inserted just off center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Garnish with bacon curls and parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp and chicken saute
directions: Coat a large skillet with cooking spray, add 1 tablespoon of olive oil and place over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook until it turns white and begins to brown.
Add shrimp; sprinkle on salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring frequently, until chicken is lightly brown and shrimp is pink.
Using a slotted spoon, remove chicken and shrimp; set aside.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche dish with pastry.
Prick bottom and sides with a fork.
Bake at 300° for 3 to 4 minutes.
Cook spinach; drain water.
Combine remaining ingredients in a mixing bowl. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until peanut butter is melted.
Pour over popcorn, stirring to coat.
(Two spoons or rubber spatulas work best.)

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Beat well.
Add zucchini.
Mix together all dry ingredients (except chips) in a separate bowl and then add creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake in 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: uncooked coconut candy
directions: Melt oleo.
Combine all ingredients, except chocolate bits and paraffin, and add to oleo.
Mix well by hands.
Form into small balls on wax paper to harden in refrigerator.

title: peach jelly
directions: Cook peaches and sugar together for 20 minutes.
Then stir in jello.
Put in jars and seal or freeze.

title: kare's chicken
directions: Skin chicken.
Cook it in microwave until done.
Mix all ingredients together and marinate chicken in mixture for up to 24 hours.
Heat chicken on grill, basting often with the mixture.

title: frosted cream cookies
directions: Knead in flour to roll easily, approximately 5 to 6 cups flour.
Use your favorite cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies should be cool before frosting.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, which have been beaten until lemon colored.
Combine flavorings; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and flour.
Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together and form loaf.
Pour can of tomato soup over top of loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in flour and cocoa.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour baked beans(10 to 12 servings)
directions: In wide frying pan, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp. Lift out, drain, crumble and set aside.
Discard all but 1/4 cup of drippings.
Add onions to drippings, separating onions into rings. Stir in brown sugar, mustard and vinegar; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until juices are reduced by half (about 10 minutes).
Drain butter beans, kidney beans and 1 can of pork and beans.
Combine with the undrained can of pork and beans in a 3 to 3 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add onion-vinegar mixture and bacon. Stir gently until blended.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly (1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: chili sauce
directions: Grind peppers and onions and boil in sugar, salt and vinegar for 20 minutes.
Add cut up tomatoes.
Cook for 1 to 2 hours.
Add spices and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Bottle hot.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Combine fruit and nuts; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream butter; beat well.
Mix part of dry ingredients with fruit; add rest of ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in fruit.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bacon-tomato dip
directions: Mix all together.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in boiler and boil hard for 3 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla flavoring.
Have ready the oats and nuts; pour into boiling mixture after it has boiled for 3 minutes and stir.
Remove from heat immediately and drop onto wax paper by teaspoonful.
Let cool.
These may seem sticky, but they will dry out.
Do not refrigerate.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Mix sugar, water, raisins, shortening, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt.
Boil 10 minutes.
Let cool; add flour and soda. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Very moist.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix Pioneer mix, brown sugar, cinnamon, butter, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Add blueberries.
Pour batter into paper lined muffin tins, 2/3 full. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until lightly browned on tops.

title: sukujaki
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, lower to simmer and cook 10 to 15 minutes. Add 1/2 pound bean sprouts or 1 can, drained. Serve over rice.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Microwave onion and celery in a little water for 4 minutes and drain.
Mix all ingredients and add as much mayonnaise as you like.
Refrigerate overnight; it will taste better.

title: apple oat bread(no fat and cholesterol)
directions: Spray loaf pan with Pam.
Mix oats and next 4 ingredients. In small bowl, beat honey, milk, oil and egg whites until blended. Stir into flour mixture just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fold in apples.
Spoon into loaf pan.
Bake 65 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cook in pan 10 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Bake in 11 x 7-inch greased and floured pan in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: seaton salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Finely chop onion; add to cooked macaroni.
Peel and cut cucumbers in circle slices and add half to macaroni.
Cut and remove insides of tomatoes.
Slice and dice, then add to macaroni.
Chop celery into thin slices.
Add Miracle Whip.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir all ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Great for church buffet.
Double ingredients for larger parties.

title: pecan loaf
directions: Use a fine blade of the grinder for the first four ingredients.
Mix all ingredients.
Pack into a greased pan (7 1/2 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/4-inch).
Cover with a foil and bake in a preheated 350° oven about 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.
Slice and serve hot with a mushroom sauce.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Blend cucumber and onion with cottage cheese and cream cheese. Add salt, pepper, red pepper and Worcestershire sauce.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Add eggs and yellow peppers.
Put in glass jar.

title: pineapple cheese mold
directions: Combine cheese and butter.
Slowly beat in liquids.
Scrape down sides of bowl often.
Beat until well blended.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Shape cheese into pineapple shape. Flatten top and cover with wax paper or foil.
Chill several hours. Allow time for following:
mark cheese with toothpicks, forming diamond shapes.
Place clove in center of each diamond.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place pineapple crown on top, holding in with toothpicks.
Sliced olives may be used instead of cloves.
Serves 25 or 30.

title: oven omelet(for company brunch)
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, beat eggs, sour cream and milk until well blended.
Stir in ham. Arrange cheese on bottom of pan and pour in mixture.
Bake 35 minutes or until set, but still moist.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine and mix pretzels, pecans and sugar together. Press in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool and chill.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Will keep for 2 weeks or bake as soon as mixed.
Bake at 500° for 8 minutes.

title: green beans with water chestnuts
directions: Stir-fry beans, water chestnuts, mushrooms and garlic in oils. Add the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until beans are tender, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spray Pam on cookie sheet.
Roll out crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350 oven for 12 minutes-let cool.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
I bake in a sheet cake pan.
Cut into 2 parts.
Crumble 1/2 of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Prepare 1 package of pudding mix.
Pour the 1 prepared pudding mix over the 1/2 of cake.

Add 1 can of drained pineapple, 1 can of coconut, 1 package of thawed, drained whole strawberries and 1 Cool Whip. Start over with the other half of cake and add the same amount of ingredients, alternating them.
Top with the last container of Cool Whip.
Top with nuts and cherries.

title: pepperoni rolls(makes approximately 45 rolls)
directions: Dissolve yeast in a little warm water.
Set aside.
Add warm water, shortening, sugar, salt and powdered milk together.
Let cool.
Add yeast to mixture.
Add flour and mix together.
Grease bottom of pan and dough.
Cover and let rise until double.
Divide into rolls.
Put 4 to 5 slices of pepperoni in each roll.
(I use a little Mozzarella cheese.)
Then roll up and place on greased pans.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Blend first 9 ingredients together.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and brown in 1/4 cup shortening.
Drain well. Combine jelly and chili sauce in saucepan; heat on low heat.
Add drained meatballs to mixture.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve in warmer-type dish.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Mix cooked ground beef, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and torn up bread.
Stuff mixture into noodles.
Cover noodles with spaghetti sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crumble
directions: Peel, core and slice the apples.
Combine the water, sugar and lemon rind in a saucepan.
Add the apple slices and cook, covered, until soft.
Put into a well-buttered pie tin.

title: lasagne in a bun
directions: Cut thin slice off tops of buns.
Hollow out centers, leaving 1/2-inch thick shells.
Set aside.
Reserve bread crumbs for another use.
In skillet, cook beef and drain.
Add tomato sauce, soup mix and herbs. Cook, covered, on low 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes.
In a bowl, combine egg, Ricotta or cottage cheese and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese into bottom of rolls.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese. Replace bun tops.
Wrap sandwiches individually in foil. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks and cup of milk.
Slowly stir into scalded milk and cook until thick.
Pour into oven-safe container.
If desired top with meringue, made by beating 3 egg whites until stiff; and beating in 3 heaping tablespoons sugar. Put on top and brown in 350° oven.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Add onion and hamburger and cook until browned.
Add soup and milk.
Stir well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Mix all of the ingredients together and put Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: clam cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate until firm.
Roll into a ball on waxed paper and roll into parsley flakes to cover. Refrigerate.

title: chicken, filipino-style
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Remove skin from chicken and marinate in sauce mixture for 30 minutes.
Bring chicken and sauce to boil on top of stove.
Turn heat down and simmer, covered for 45 minutes.
Turn several times during cooking.
Serve with rice.

title: plantation salad
directions: In a mixer, combine sugar, cream cheese and milk; add pineapple, pecans and Cool Whip.
Fold in gently until mixed well. Refrigerate.

title: hot wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips; pat dry.
Mix wings, red pepper and poultry seasonings.
Deep fry at 400° for 12 minutes or until completely cooked and crispy; drain.
Combine hot sauce and butter.
Dip wings in sauce to coat completely.
Serve with celery and Blue cheese dip.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Pierce and bake potatoes.
Allow potatoes to cool to the touch.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell.
Place pulp in a large bowl.

title: pecan drops
directions: Beat egg white for 5 minutes, then add vanilla, brown sugar and chopped pecans.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: paella valenciana
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces and saute the pieces in butter with clove of garlic until the chicken is a golden brown on all sides.
Remove and set aside the chicken.
To the juices remaining in the pan, add rice and saute until the rice is golden. Add saffron and hot chicken stock and cook over a very low flame until all the liquid is absorbed.
The rice will be only partly cooked.

title: bacon tidbit
directions: Mix eggs with vinegar. Mix cracker crumbs with mustard and red pepper.
Take each 1/3 bacon slice and dip in egg. Then coat with crumbs.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Can be cooked beforehand and reheated or frozen, thawed and reheated.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Chop garlic fine and add all ingredients.
Cook slow for 1 hour or until thick.

title: jamaican junk casserole
directions: Brown the sausage; drain, saving 3 tablespoons of fat.
Saute the onion, green pepper and celery in reserved drippings.
Pour water over soup mix.
Combine all ingredients except the almonds. Place in a large baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle buttered almonds over the top.
Return to oven and bake, uncovered, for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Measure into mixing bowl warm water.
Add, stirring to dissolve, dry yeast.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and 3 cups flour.
Mix with spoon until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to handle easily.
Mix with hand.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Round up in greased bowl, greased side up.
Cover with damp cloth.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Punch down; let rise again until almost double.
Divide dough for desired rolls; shape.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Amount:
1 large coffee cake or 1 1/2 to 2 dozen rolls.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion together.
Drain well.
Fry tortillas until soft.
Roll meat into them.
Lay into a shallow baking dish.
Melt cheese, soup and milk together until smooth. Add pimentos and chilies.
Pour cheese mixture over tortillas and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes very rich and attractive dish for guests.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix together the following and spread on cooled bread:
cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise.
Chop green peppers, celery, carrots, onion, cauliflower and broccoli.
Mix together and place on top of cream cheese.
(May also be mixed with cream cheese.) Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate.
Cut in squares.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes, until cookies test done with toothpick.
Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute, then remove to rack to finish cooling.

title: coconut fried shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Combine pancake flour with beer; stir until smooth.
Dredge shrimp in flour, dip into batter, then dredge in the coconut.
Deep-fry a few at a time (if using electric fryer, set at 350°).
Cook until golden brown, about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve as appetizer or main for 2.

title: crab butter
directions: Cream together first 7 ingredients
add 1 1/2 cups crab meat. Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
This is good on different kinds of crackers.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocados in chunks and put them in a blender.
Add all ingredients except tomatoes.
Blend well.
Add tomatoes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add melted butter and blend.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: mock whipped cream
directions: Put in blender and blend until whipped.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Dot hashbrowns with 1 stick butter. Mix mushroom soup, sour cream and onion together. Spread on top of potatoes. Top with cheddar cheese, crushed corn flakes and drizzle with 1 stick of melted butter. Bake at 350 degrees for 90 minutes.

title: chicken nicoise
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Heat half the oil in skillet.
Brown chicken pieces well on all sides.
Remove and keep warm.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring sugar, salt, margarine, cocoa and milk to a full, rolling boil; boil 2 minutes in a 3-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until melted.
Add oats; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix sausage, ricotta, mozzarella, cream cheese, spinach, hot pepper sauce until well blended. Fill pie crust with sausage mixture. Make decorative cut out pastry - place on top. Bake at 400 degrees 30 to 40 minutes or until brown. Serve warm or room temp. Will make 2 pies.

title: no name dessert
directions: Mix margarine and flour.
Line pan; press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Mix pudding and milk.
Beat until thick and spread over cooled crust.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over top.
Coconut or sliced bananas may be added to top.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine the sweetened condensed milk and the beaten egg yolks. Gradually add the lime juice and mix thoroughly.
Fill the prebaked pie shell	or
graham
cracker
shell
with
the mixture. Bake in a 350°
oven
for	8
to 10 minutes.
Do not allow to brown.
Chill
the	pie
in
the
refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Whip
the cream and then garnish with rosettes of whipped cream.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Oil baking sheets (lightly).
Combine oil, sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Add egg.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Stir in flour, salt and baking soda until mixture is smooth.
Blend in milk.
Drop by teaspoonful onto baking sheets.
Flatten cookies with bottom of glass lightly oiled and dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes or until browned around edges.
Remove to cooling rack. Makes 3 dozen.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a graham cracker pie crust and put into refrigerator to chill.
Top with pecans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with crumbs.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes, also can be microwaved.

title: coffee fudge
directions: Bring to a boil in large, heavy pan.
Remove from heat until dissolved:
sugar, cream, butter, salt and cream of tarter.
Cook, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Cover and cook 3 minutes. Uncover and cook over moderate heat.
Add almond extract or cinnamon.
Beat until mixture starts to harden.
Add nuts.
Pour onto buttered surface.
Permit the candy to cool and harden before cutting into squares.

title: shrimp or crab meat salad
directions: Cook pasta shells in salted water. Drain.
Combine all ingredients except salad dressing in bowl.
Mix in enough salad dressing to moisten to desired consistency. Sprinkle with paprika. Chill overnight or for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: marge's marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May be used as a marinade for chicken or beef.
Chicken or beef should remain in marinade for at least 3 hours before barbecuing.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Mix and pour into crust and chill.

title: 5 pound fruit cake
directions: Chop candied fruit in small pieces; add to pecans.
Set aside. Mix the first 7 items in a large mixing bowl.
Mix by hand only and only until all items are wet.
It's okay to have lumps.
If you mix too much, you'll need a steak knife to cut the cake.
Take the fruit and pecans and add the flour; coat the fruit well, then fold into cake mixture.
Put mixture in 2 loaf pans and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Place a pan of water under the cakes while baking.

title: traditional chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat margarine in shallow roasting pan in oven until melted.
Remove; stir in salt and Worcestershire. Add cereals and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Heat in oven 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Can also add some pretzel sticks.
